title: christmas poinsettias
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the powdered sugar and butter until smooth.
Blend in eggs, vanilla and rum extract.
Stir together the flour and salt.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in coconut and 3/4 cup butterscotch chips.
Chill dough until firm.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Work in shortening, yeast and buttermilk.
Knead and roll on floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter; fold in half. Spread top with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: mom's sweet dough
directions: For apple, rhubarb, blueberry, cherry, pear, peach, pineapple or strawberry pie.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and put over chicken in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mom's hearty bacon casserole
directions: Reserve four slices of bacon.
Cut remainder into 1/2-inch slices (use kitchen shears).
Fry until crisp, then remove from pan.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons drippings until soft.
Combine onions, crisp bacon, macaroni, cheese and milk.
Mix lightly and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Place reserved slices on top and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in rest of ingredients with fork. Great with crackers.

title: last minute crab casserole
directions: In medium bowl mix mayonnaise, soup and milk.
Stir in crabmeat and noodles.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: st. john's club kale soup
directions: Heat the olive oil in a heavy 8-quart stockpot over high heat. Add the sausage and onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Add the garlic, parsley and beans. Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Add the chicken stock and bring to a boil. Add the bay leaves, thyme and the crushed red pepper. Season again with salt and black pepper. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer, uncovered, until the beans are tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Add the potatoes and kale; season with salt and pepper. Continue to simmer for another 30 minutes. Skim off any fat that rises to the surface. Remove the bay leaves.

title: kolacky(polish pastry)
directions: Knead and work with pastry blender the flour, baking powder, sugar and butter.
Add eggs; blend.
Add sour cream; blend.
Dough is sticky, so cool in refrigerator.
Roll dough out very thin over confectioners sugar (also can coat rolling pin with pastry sleeve in confectioners sugar; never use flour).
Cut out dough into triangles.
Spread a little of the filling over the triangles and roll them up.
The filling must be thick, or it will run.
Put rolls on ungreased cookie sheet (Teflon).
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, or until light tan on bottom.
Powder sugar them when cool or right before eating.
(Just roll or toss them in powdered sugar.)

title: strawberries
directions: Mix together all ingredients; chill.
Remove a small amount of mixture from refrigerator at a time, form into small balls and shape into strawberries.
Roll in 1/2 cup pink tinted sugar.
Dip stem in 1/2 cup green tinted sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well and pour in a large greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix well and add to starter.
Let starter stand out of refrigerator all day (8 to 12 hours) or until very bubbly.
Remove 1 cup to make bread and return remaining to the refrigerator. Keep in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days and feed again.
If not making bread after feeding starter, throw away 1 cup, but it may be fed 2 to 3 times before using for any bread.
This is to avoid depleting your starter.

title: aunt kath's "perfect" chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, beat well, mix in flour and soda. Add chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix and bring to boil syrup, sugar and cream of tartar.
When forms soft ball, remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Pour over popcorn and form into balls.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and garlic in a large saucepan. Add water to cover. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and return potatoes and garlic to pan. Beat at medium speed of a mixer 1 minute or until smooth. Add sour cream and remaining ingredients; beat until well blended. Makes 4 servings.

title: sauerkraut with pork
directions: Brown pork in skillet.
Mix sauerkraut with brown sugar and place in large crock-pot.
Add meat.
Cook on low setting for 7 to 9 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, soups, milk and mushrooms together in a casserole dish.
Evenly distribute Stove Top stuffing on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: In a saucepan put sugar and syrup and bring to a full rolling boil;
remove from heat and add peanut butter and cereal of choice.
Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper, cool.
Easy and very yummy!!

title: sweet and sour chicken marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Soak chicken 2 to 3 hours.
Place chicken and liquid into skillet.
Cook until chicken is tender.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil and blend in eggs. Mix together with the rest of the ingredients. Pour into bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add buttermilk, to which soda has been added, eggs, vanilla, oil and jam.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Makes 3 round 9-inch layers.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll and press together refrigerated crescent rolls onto baking pan until bottom of pan is covered, then bake until golden brown.
When cooled, spread mixture of Ranch dip (made with sour cream) on rolls.
Top with finely chopped veggies (of choice); sprinkle Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Makes a great appetizer!

title: deep south pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oil, 2 tablespoons at a time. Add eggs, one at a time, beating slightly after each other.
Add lemon juice and rind and salt.
Add the milk and flour alternately, ending with flour.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Fold in vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put crackers and peanut butter in mixing bowl; mix together. Bring to full rolling boil sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla. Pour over cracker mix.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until very creamy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add flour, slowly beating until mixed.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. In a large bowl measure all ingredients, except raisins, walnuts and 10x sugar.
With mixer on low, beat until well mixed, constantly scraping bowl with spatula.
Beat at high speed 3 minutes.
If you like, stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour in pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack and then sprinkle with 10x sugar, if you desire.

title: onion and cucumber salad
directions: Cut cukes and onions as thin as possible.
Mix equal parts of Hellmann's mayonnaise and sour cream (about 1/2 cup each, or more if you want it).
Add white vinegar and sugar.
Mix all this together.
Refrigerate for awhile.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make loaf and smother with tomato paste. Top with strips of bacon, if desired.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zesty beet and orange salad
directions: Drain and rinse beets.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Remove peel and pith from 2 oranges; cut into rounds.
Arrange beet and orange slices on a lettuce-lined serving platter, if desired. Zest and juice remaining orange.
In small bowl, whisk together 1 teaspoon zest, 2 tablespoons orange juice, chopped red onion, extra virgin olive oil and balsamic vinegar.
Drizzle citrus dressing over beet-orange salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Blend well.
Toss with 1 cup croutons and 2 heads Romaine lettuce.

title: lemon lite delight
directions: Combine flour, margarine and pecans in bowl.
Mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and half the whipped topping in bowl until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine pudding mix and milk in bowl; beat until slightly thickened.
Pour over cream mixture. Top with remaining whipped topping.
Chill, covered, for at least 2 hours.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine butter and peanut butter in a glass bowl. Cover with a paper towel and microwave on high for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in graham cracker crumbs ad powdered sugar. Press into 11 x 17 x 1 1/2 inch baking dish. Microwave on medium for
2 minutes or until melted. Stir well and spread over peanut butter mixture. Cover and chill. Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: festive crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: cabbage for non-cabbage lovers
directions: In deep skillet lightly brown bacon. Add in layers cabbage, apple, Natures Seasoning and repeat until all ingredients are used. Simmer uncovered 20-30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mixed up sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add cheese and soup.
Cut up olives. Add all ingredients together and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put mixture on closed buns in aluminum foil or open-faced for crunchier sandwiches.
Makes 18 open-faced sandwiches.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground hamburger with chopped onion. Place Tater Tots in bottom of casserole dish. Heat soups and pour over hamburger and Tater Tots. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Break lettuce into small pieces.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer next 5 ingredients on lettuce.
Spread Miracle Whip like frosting on top.
Sprinkle sugar over Miracle Whip.
Layer cheese then bacon over all.
Cover.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: curried pumpkin mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until onions are soft.
Add flour and curry.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken stock and continue stirring.
Stir in pumpkin and honey. Serve with white sauce or milk, stirred in.
Sprinkle with pinch of grated nutmeg.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Trim excess fat and remove membranes from pork.
Mix catsup, brown sugar, lemon juice, salt, garlic powder and ginger; pour over pork, turning to coat both sides.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Let remain in oven and allow to cool with oven.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan. Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Baste occasionally.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs and sugar; add pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Top with pecans.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn out onto towel sprinkled solidly with powdered sugar.
Roll in towel and cool.

title: light waffles
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda in a large bowl.
Combine buttermilk and oil; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until "just" moistened.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; carefully fold into batter.
Coat a waffle iron with cooking spray and allow waffle iron to preheat.
Pour batter onto hot waffle iron and bake.
Yield:
32 (4-inch) waffles.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, margarine, shortening, egg and molasses. Mix dry ingredients (salt, cinnamon, allspice, ginger, soda and flour). Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Drop on cookie sheet with spoon. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown on edges.

title: ethel click's cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, onion and green pepper; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients and let stand until sugar dissolves. Mix well with cabbage mixture.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: sweet pecan pancakes
directions: Beat ingredients with wire whisk or hand beater.
Mixture should pour out of ladle onto hot griddle; cook until light golden brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine browned ground beef and spaghetti sauce.
In casserole dish, layer macaroni, sauce and cheese.
Before adding last layer of cheese, add one layer of pepperoni slices. Bake in a 350° oven until hot and until cheese has melted (about 30 minutes).

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing until well blended.
Spread tortillas with 1/8-inch cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with finely chopped peppers and olives.
Roll up tightly.
When ready to serve, serve, slice into 1/2-inch sections.
Then arrange pinwheel style on serving plate.

title: moravian christmas cookies
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Add the sugar and mix well.
Cut in butter and lard with a pastry blender or 2 knives. Add the molasses and vinegar gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Chill several hours.
Using a small amount of dough at a time, roll out about 1/8-inch thick on a floured surface.
Cut with fancy cookie cutters.
Transfer to greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and make into ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: german potato salad
directions: Saute bacon and onion until transparent.
Add vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper.
(Bacon should be cut into small crosswise strips before it is cooked.)
Mix cornstarch with water to thin paste and stir into other ingredients.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add diced, cooked potatoes and serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Fry bacon; drain and cut up. Drain all beans.
Mix all ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 hours.

title: fourth of july cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour.
Pour batter into three prepared 9-inch cake pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then cool completely before frosting.

title: california enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix in saucepan the tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon hot pepper sauce and garlic powder.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: Mix everything together in small saucepan.
Cook until it boils; stir 1 minute longer.
Pour over baked ham 1/2 hour before ready to take from oven.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Freeze for 24 hours. Take out of freezer 2 hours before serving. Serve mushy. Makes 3 quarts.

title: luscious low-cal cheesecake
directions: Spray spring-form pan with Pam cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put graham cracker crumbs, sugar, cinnamon and 1 egg white into bowl of food processor, pulse 5 times.
Press mixture into pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Place 1/2 cup cottage cheese in blender, blend until smooth.
Combine with cream cheese in large mixing bowl. Gradually beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and lemon peel.
Gradually beat in 1 egg white at a time.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 300° or until tester inserted comes out clean.
Let cool and top with cherry pie filling, strawberries or your favorite topping.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: vegetable sandwich roll
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook 2 minutes or until tender.
Stir in broccoli and water; cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook 1 minute to evaporate liquid.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, walnuts and Parmesan cheese.
Let the mixture cool.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and chop apples.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add sugar, shortening and vanilla to eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together in another bowl.
Add dry ingredients and apples to the first mixture.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: a la microwave quickie fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Add milk and butter.
Do not mix the milk and butter, merely place in the bowl. Cook 2 minutes.
Remove bowl from oven and stir just to mix ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir until blended.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine.
Add sugar and then eggs.
Mix in milk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with graham cracker crumbs and cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage into wedges lengthwise, trying to leave a small piece of the core on each slice.
Blanch in boiling water (salted) until cabbage is just beginning to become tender.
Remove, cool and drain.
Mix flour and salt well.
Add eggs and milk as needed to consistency, so batter clings to cabbage.
Dip wedges in batter and fry.

title: italian beef
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven and roast, covered, for 3 to 4 hours.
Baste frequently until cooked through.

title: candied yams
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over potatoes in shallow pan.
Cook in 350° oven until candied.

title: steak oriental
directions: Cut meat into 8 pieces.
Brown meat.
Transfer meat to casserole.
Top with vegetables.
Combine gravy and soy sauce; pour over vegetables.
Cover; cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: cookie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 1 egg.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix ingredients in order listed. Add lemon juice to bananas before adding to mixture.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Very good.

title: unbeandle diet chili
directions: In a wok or cast-iron skillet, stir-fry the ingredients at high heat until beef is done.
Drain liquid; add the tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Soften	the
yeast
in the 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Set aside. In another bowl, combine the 1 1/4 cups boiling water, oats, molasses,
shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.	Add the beaten
eggs
and
yeast mixture.
Beat well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough, 5 or 6 cups.
Knead, adding flour as needed. Place dough in greased bowl, cover and let rise in warm place until
double.
Punch down and form into 2 loaves. Grease 2
loaf pans.
Let	rise
again
until double in size, about 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: harvest time
directions: Brown beef; add onions, salt, pepper and rice.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Add soup and water; mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat; place cabbage in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shipwreck
directions: Combine tomatoes, beans, onion and bell pepper. Layer half of potato in a baking dish. Top with half of beef and half of tomato mixture. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, removing lid to boil off liquid, if necessary.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Cut fat off chops and melt.
Flour pork chops and brown.
Cut onion into fourths; slice bell pepper.
Mix wine, ketchup, garlic, pineapple, bell pepper and onion.
Put in pot with meat.
Cook until done at 350°.

title: four layer cherry cheese delight
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and pecans; spread with fingers in pan and bake until light brown at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: peach custard
directions: Blend and cook until thickened.
Pour over a large bowl of sliced peaches.
Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: jan's scalloped corn
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to a soft boiling stage.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir until mix begins to change color.
Then drop immediately on wax paper.

title: grandma's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, margarine and salt until warm.
Add flour mixture; add eggs.
Beat together. stir in as much of remaining flour as possible.
then knead in enough more to make a moderate soft dough.
Let rise.
Punch down; let rise again.
Divide in half.
Roll on board, about 2 feet long and 6 to 8-inches wide.
Pour melted butter and sprinkle cinnamon, sugar and raisins.
Roll up and slice.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise.
Place 1 tablespoon water in between rolls and bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Drain carrots, mix all other ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour over carrots and refrigerate overnight.
Heat before serving. Serves 7.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add plain flour, a little at a time, until dough is stiff. Refrigerate overnight. Cut into rolls and let rise. Cook at 350° until done.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, lemon juice, lemon peel, vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended. Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are set and edges are golden brown. Watch closely so coconut doesn't burn.
Cool for 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Then remove to foil to cool completely.

title: jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large covered casserole dish (ovenproof).
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Stir after 30 minutes.
Do not add water.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Place fruit in bottom of greased dish.
Cover with sugar mixture.
Mix batter of remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spoon over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: norwegian julekar(christmas bread)
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, butter and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast mix and 3 cups flour.
Let rise 1 hour.
Add cardamom and beaten eggs.
Mix candied fruit and raisins with 1/4 cup flour. Add to dough. Add just enough flour to handle.
Knead dough well on floured surface. Let rise until light.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Cook yellow sweet potatoes until done.
Run through Foley food mill.
Add 1/2 cup shortening to 2 cups warm sweet potatoes.
Mix well.
Add sugar, sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Roll out on floured board.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. May be frozen.
Makes about 2 dozen biscuits.

title: chocolate pie(for those who can't have milk or eggs.)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Pour into boiling water and cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Stir until blended.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Whipped topping may be added on top.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Combine
sugars,
egg
and
butter
and beat well.
Add soda, milk, bananas and flour, then blend.
Bake at 350° until brown about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: beef enchilada casserole(servings:  12)
directions: Spread the taco meat on bottom of 10 x 13 1/2 x 1/2-inch baking pan or Pyrex dish.
Cover with chopped onions.
Layer the tortillas; cover sparingly with the mixed soup and enchilada sauce.
Cover this with sliced tamales and cover with rest of sauce.
Sprinkle all over with green chilies.
Cover tightly with foil and put in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil.
Cover with cheese.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: diabetic salad
directions: Drain juice off of pineapple and put to the side for later use.
Mix jello according to directions on box.
Add drained pineapple and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: five layer cream dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts like pie crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Mix together pudding and milk and pour over Cool Whip layer.
Spread other 1/2 carton of Cool Whip over pudding layer.
May top with nuts.

title: shrimp party mold
directions: Soften gelatin in milk.
Heat soup and cream cheese until melted.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into lightly greased 4-cup mold.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.
May also mold in individual molds and served as salad.
(May substitute chicken for shrimp and use cream of chicken soup. Dilute curry powder.)
Yields 4 cups.

title: braised beef with mahogany onions
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put uncooked bacon, onion and garlic in a large casserole.
Place roast on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until tender, turning beef halfway through cooking time.
Slice roast across grain, top with onion mixture and serve.
Reheats well.

title: cheezy potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Place in baking dish. Add sliced onions, salt, pepper, cheese and milk.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's brown bread
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add raisins, butter and soda.
Remove from the heat.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir into raisin mixture.
Grease 3 (16 ounce) vegetable or fruit cans.
Divide batter between cans and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until breads test done.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from cans. Cool on a wire rack.

title: french toast apple casserole
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add apples and raisins; toss to coat well.
Spread mixture evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Arrange slices of bread on top.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla, salt and 2 teaspoons cinnamon until well blended.
Pour mixture over bread, soaking bread completely.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 24 hours. Bake, covered, in a preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes. Serve warm.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with salts and seed.
Place in marinade pan or cooking bag if no pan.
Pour smoke over meat to coat all surfaces. Flip pan from time to time.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Halve tomatoes and trim ends so they lie flat in pan.
Put in buttered pan.
Mix dry ingredients and melted margarine.
Pat on tomatoes firmly.
(Especially delicious when Maryland tomatoes are used.)
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together in order that they are listed.
Put in casserole and serve.
It can also be used as a topping for a plain cake.

title: congo bars
directions: Whip sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Fold in dry ingredients, then add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sunrise coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; cream together well.
Add all the other ingredients alternately with the milk.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Place in refrigerator overnight before baking.

title: mamie's plain cake
directions: With cake upside down, slice entire top about 1 inch down from two 10-inch high cakes.
Shell out cake, leaving 1 inch walls and sides.
Save tops.

title: chocolate chip, date nut cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates and cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and dates.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa and add.
Mix well, pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips, 1/4 cup sugar over batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cool cooked chicken and cut into cubes.
Mix all together.

title: scrumptious brunch casserole
directions: Will need an 8-inch square Pyrex pan (greased).

title: taco hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning mix.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer ingredients as follows:
corn chips, hamburger mixture, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and cheese.
Layer twice.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or 45 minutes, until done.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown peppers, garlic, onions, and meat in bacon drippings. Add other ingredients except spaghetti and cook approximately 1-1/2 hours.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put lard, sugar, salt and baking powder in hot milk.
When cool, stir in yeast mixture.
Add flour to make soft dough. Cover and let rise once.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Let rise again.
Roll out on floured surface and bake at 400°.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Break up breads.
Mix everything together, except margarine. Pour into crock-pot and dot top with margarine.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or on high for 2 hours.
Makes 16 servings. Cook chicken and use the broth from it instead of canned broth.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Place apples in a buttered casserole dish.
Cream margarine, sugar and flour.
Add cheese.
Mix.
Spoon over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chips of chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend flour, brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Remove 1 cup.
To remaining crumb mixture, in a mixer bowl, add baking powder, soda, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
After cooling 15 minutes, may be drizzled with thin powdered sugar icing.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg and milk and add to flour, powder, salt, butter and sugar.
Makes great pancakes.

title: romanian eggplant dip
directions: Eggplant preparation:
Cook eggplant in microwave on high for 20 minutes uncovered, poke several holes in it with a fork before cooking.
When eggplant is cooked it will deflate.
Or you may place the eggplant in the oven whole on a baking dish, bake until soft, about 1 1/2 hours, or until it splits open.
Tear open with a fork and allow steam to escape.
Cut away stem.
Place the eggplant in a food processor adding oil, parsley, lemon juice, and garlic. When mixture is well chopped add basil and pine nuts and stir. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with you favorite veggies or on bread and crackers.

title: ham and peas spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta; drain and set aside.
Saute ham in melted butter for 1 minute, then add peas.
Stir until all is covered with butter.
Add cream and bring to a boil.
Add pasta and mix well. Season.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: no cook coconut pastel bonbons
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape dough into small balls and roll in coconut or nuts. Line plate with wax paper and place balls on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake per directions on package in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool.
Prepare pudding in a mixer with cold milk.
After beating well with mixer on low/medium speed, put in small pieces of cream cheese until well blended (little chunks of cream cheese will remain in the pudding).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and butter.
Add other ingredients; cook slow until thick.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, butter and milk and heat over medium high heat for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla before taking off stove.
After taking off, add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop with spoon on wax paper.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Gradually stir in juice from peaches. Add peaches and almond extract.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch cake pan onto raw pie crust and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: husband's delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown ground beef and garlic in butter.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper and sugar.
Blend the cheeses and add sour cream, onions and green pepper to the cheese mixture.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole, put half of cooked noodles, then a layer of cheese mixture and then rest of the noodles.
Cover with beef mixture and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place cooked and diced chicken in 8 x 13-inch casserole and sprinkle with 1/2 package of Doritos, crushed.
Mix Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, diced onion, garlic salt and red pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with 1/2 package of Doritos.
Cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Add 1 teaspoon of coconut flavoring and 2/3 of one 6 ounce package of coconut to cake mix.
Bake cake as directed on box. (Use 9 x 13-inch pans.)
Remove cake from oven; punch holes through top.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients; let dough stand overnight before baking. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can keep dough in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Spread out triangles as directed on can.
Place 1/2 of a hot dog or whole hot dog (depending on preference) on triangle and roll as directed on can.
Bake following same directions.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into meatballs.
(Don't worry about the consistency as they will hold shape well.) Add meatballs to Cocktail Meatball Sauce and cook for 1 hour over low heat.

title: good stuff
directions: Mix together and coat with 1 pound white chocolate (melted). Spoon on wax paper.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° (low) for 40 minutes or until done.

title: no bake chocolate fudge cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter together.
Cook over medium heat; add vanilla and oats.
Drop onto waxed paper to cool.
May add a handful of marshmallows to keep cookies from getting too hard.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir to a full all-over boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils slowly 3 minutes.
Take off heat.
Stir in all at once peanuts. Beat until candy starts to thicken.
Drop from teaspoons onto waxed paper to form 24 clusters.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain and put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Put cream of mushroom soup on meat.
Top with chopped onion.
Put a layer of cheese over onion.
Top with cream of celery soup.
Put thin layer of cheese on soup and top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Toss first 8 ingredients together.
Put in baking dish. Mix Pepperidge Farm stuffing
with
melted butter.
Put on top for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream margarine in mixing bowl until light.
Sift in confectioners sugar gradually, beating constantly, until light and fluffy.
Add condensed milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.
Melt chocolate with paraffin in double boiler over hot water.
Mix well.
Dip candy balls
on toothpick into chocolate.
Place in paper bonbon cups. Let stand until firm.

title: au gratin potato casserole
directions: Mix everything but hash browns and sour cream in a pan on top of the stove until cheese melts.
Remove and add 2 cups sour cream. Sprinkle potatoes in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Pour mixture over top. Sprinkle with buttered crushed cornflakes or bread crumbs.
Green pepper or green onions can be added for color.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.
Can assemble day before baking.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: coconut cream pies
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch well.
Mix the 2 cups evaporated milk with 2 cups of water and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Then add the well-beaten egg yolks.
Stir well and add to the sugar and cornstarch mixture and heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add the coconut and pour into 2 lightly browned pie shells.

title: hot fudge sauce(microwave)
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, sugar and water and microwave on High for
1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Add oleo, vanilla and salt.
Microwave until thick, stirring occasionally.

title: california wine beans
directions: Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not let beans get too dry.
Serve with sour cream and chopped green onions.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out thinly.
Cut into strips, then cut again.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 250°.

title: fast and easy hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 9 x 13 baking pan for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cheddar cheese pork chops
directions: Pour water into 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle pork chops with seasoned salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Arrange in baking dish.
Top with cheese, onion and soup.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Use liquid in baking dish as sauce.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add chocolate and salt.
Add water.
Cook until thick and then remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Makes enough for one 9 inch square cake or one loaf cake.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat whipping cream until thick.
Add other ingredients and mix together well.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Finish with whole milk.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine milk, lemonade and limeade until well blended.
Slowly add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate until sets. Will keep 2 weeks.

title: vegetable confetti soup
directions: Heat oil in 6-quart pot.
Add onions; cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Add carrots, fennel, stock, tarragon and thyme.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, until veggies are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add red pepper, zucchini and mushrooms. Cook, covered, for 10 minutes more.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot garnished with Parmesan cheese.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cutout sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well mixed.
Shape dough into ball. Wrap and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours, until easy to handle.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 to 4 heaping teaspoonfuls in a cup of hot water.

title: coconut pies
directions: Butter the crust; spread on coconut.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs, melted butter, vanilla and milk.
Pour over coconut.
Bake at 375° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen and used when needed.

title: pecan pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook on 325° for 45 minutes.

title: quick no bake oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Combine sugar and butter in a medium saucepan and heat, stirring until blended.
Stir in cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove pan from heat and stir in vanilla.
Let mixture cool 5 minutes.
Blend in oats, salt, chopped nuts and flaked coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Roll chicken breasts in flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt mixture. Insert thin ham slice and Swiss cheese slice into each chicken breast; roll up. Close flap with toothpicks. Place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour can of chicken soup over chicken breasts. Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Beat all ingredients well and cook in long pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Make icing and pour on cake while it's hot.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt chips, oleo and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Stir to coat completely.
Place powdered sugar in large sack.
Dump in cereal mixture.
Shake until coated.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Place bread slices in food processor with metal blade or a blender.
Process or blend to form 1 cup crumbs.
Set aside.
Peel rutabaga and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Put into saucepan with enough water to cover; simmer over low heat until very soft, about 20 minutes.
Drain well and puree in food processor or blender. (Should make 2 cups of puree.) Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Put rutabaga in large bowl and add remaining ingredients in order listed, adding bread crumbs after the salt and pepper, mixing well.
Pour into prepared casserole and bake in middle of oven at 375° for approximately 40 minutes, until mixture is slightly puffed and lightly browned on top.
Makes 6 servings (145 calories per serving).
Can be successfully reheated.

title: slice and bake cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to the creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups extras.
Shape into a 15 inch x 2 inch roll; wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Chill 2 hours or up to a week.
Unwrap and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool completely. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all into large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Chill one hour.

title: strawberry yogurt whip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add yogurt and beat with mixer until mixture is light and fluffy.
Pour into serving dishes.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: picnic relish
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oil over medium heat until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Cool. Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fried turkey
directions: You will need a 16-quart pot, thermometer and an outdoor propane cooker.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to margarine mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake 40 minutes in loaf pan at 350°.

title: jiffy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground meats in fat in a skillet on a heat minder at 350°.
Sprinkle the dry onion mix and ginger over the meat. Arrange the noodles in a layer over the meat.
Add mushrooms with the liquid.
Pour hot water over the noodles, making sure all the noodles are moistened.
Cover tightly.
Turn heat minder to 225° and cook 20 minutes or until noodles are done.
Blend flour into sour cream and stir into stroganoff.
Cook about 3 minutes longer until thickened.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
If desired, 2 tablespoons sherry may be added just before serving.

title: corn light bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Spoon into a well-greased l0-inch tube pan; let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 12-15.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients (except 1/2 cup grated cheese) and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Sift 1 cup flour and baking soda into bowl.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter until crumbly.
Stir in flour, coconut and oatmeal.
Press firmly into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, 6 ounces chocolate chips, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup walnuts, 1/4 cup melted butter and 1 teaspoon flour.
Pour over bottom layer. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Delicious!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer in a punch bowl the cake, vanilla pudding, Cool Whip and fresh fruit. Repeat these layers. This will completely fill a punch bowl. Be sure you have the Cool Whip on top.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat 2 c. of tomato juice to dissolve jello.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Set.
Note:
Shrimp or crabmeat added are delicious.

title: idiot pie
directions: Combine milk and lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil giblets in salted water until very tender.
Reserve liquid for cooking rice, adding more water, if needed.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add and beat remaining ingredients.
Sugar sprinkles can be added after dough is rolled and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: six layer dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Stir in garlic salt, garlic powder, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Spread in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Spread sour cream on top.
Drain picante sauce well.
Spoon over sour cream.
Top with olives and tomatoes, then cheese.
Makes 6 cups.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and cube. Add bouillon, soup, butter, salt and pepper. Blend flour and Crisco with a fork. Add egg; mix well. Add milk. Drop by teaspoonful into boiling stock when all the dough is in stockpot. Cover; turn stock off and let set 10 minutes. Thicken stock with cornstarch and small amount of water. Pour into stock before adding dumplings.

title: layered salad
directions: Note: First, chop all ingredients (except peas) before making salad.

title: english moussaka
directions: Fry mince and remove excess fat.
Remove from heat.
Add tomato puree, garlic to taste, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish and keep warm.
Thinly slice potatoes and fry until brown.
Place on top of meat and season.
Prepare cheese sauce (thicken a little if rather thin) and pour on top of potatoes. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and arrange sliced tomato.
Bake in moderate oven just about centre, until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve with salad or green vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: apricot salad
directions: Keep apricot and pineapple juices separate.
Chill fruit. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add apricot juice.
Fold in apricots, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add egg and butter.
Add pineapple juice; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream; spread over jello mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Chill.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl and add to the beef. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with chow mein noodles and slivered almonds.
Return to oven for 30 minutes more to crisp.

title: scrambled eggs super
directions: Mix eggs and cream. Scramble in butter. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350 degrees approximately one hour or until solid (like scrambled eggs). This can be refrigerated, uncooked, overnight and baked in the morning.

title: mexi-stew in a biscuit bowl
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Stir together first 3 ingredients. Turn dough out onto a surface sprinkled with additional biscuit mix. Shape into a ball. Knead 3 or 4 times. Divide into 6 portions. Invert 6 (6 ounce) ovenproof custard cups several inches apart on a rimmed baking sheet. Coat bottoms of cups with nonstick cooking spray. Roll or pat each dough portion into a 6-inch circle. Place each on a custard cup. Press into a bowl shape. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly. Remove biscuit bows to a wire rack. Cook ground chuck, onion and bell pepper in a Dutch oven over medium heat until meat crumbles and is no longer pink. Drain. Stir in tomatoes, beans and chili powder. Bring ground chuck mixture to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 35 minutes. Spoon into biscuit bowls and serve with desired toppings. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup, sugar
and
water.
Boil hard for 5 minutes, then add peanuts.
Let
come to a boil; fold over and over for about 5 minutes
or
until
peanuts
are golden brown.
Remove from
heat and add salt and soda. Beat hard and quickly spread on buttered surface and pull out thin while hot.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee, vanilla and milk, mix for 2 minutes (batter will be thin). Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2 in. pans
bake 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in casserole and mix with soup and 1/2 can onion rings, crumbled.
Put remaining onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: greater tater casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and spread on cheeses.
Bake for 30 minutes more or until cheese is brown.

title: baked cranberry casserole
directions: Place cranberries in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with apples and pineapple.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and pecans.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over fruits.
Pour melted margarine over all and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: punch
directions: Put bananas in blender until smooth.
Mix all together and freeze.
Take out to thaw 2 hours.
Add six (28 ounce) bottles of 7-Up.
Serves 50.

title: mountain dew pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, then the rest of the ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots crosswise in 1-inch chunks.
Cook covered in boiling salt water.
Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch and ginger. Add orange juice.
Cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter.
Drain carrots and pour mixture over hot carrots.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a 9-inch pie plate in preheated 450° oven.
Tilt plate so margarine completely covers bottom; set aside.
Beat together eggs, milk, flour 1 tablespoon sugar and salt until smooth.
Pour into hot pie plate.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Reduce to 375° and bake until golden brown and sides are puffy, about 8 minutes longer.

title: carrots gourmet
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Mix together carrots, bacon, salt, pepper and onion.
Place in 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with sugar and butter.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Combine flour and cocoa.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Add pecans.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough about 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Meanwhile unwrap Kisses.
Shape scant tablespoon of dough around Kiss, covering Kiss completely.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar again before serving, if desired.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese cake sandwiches
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place one package of rolls in cake pan.
Combine
cream
cheese,
sugar,
vanilla
and egg yolk. Cream until smooth.
Spread in pan.
Place other pack of rolls on top of cheese mixture.
Beat
egg
white
and brush on top of rolls.
Bake at 350°
for glass pan) until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour in large baking dish.
Keep check while baking, may take less time depending on your oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Mix all ingredients and pour in dish.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, syrup and water in saucepan. Stir until thick.
Add jello.

title: poppy seed bread(cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 1 greased and floured loaf pan or 3 small ones.
Bake approximately 45 minutes, until springs back when lightly touched.
Freezes well.

title: raspberry salad
directions: In double boiler, place 2 cups water; add marshmallows to water.
After marshmallows have melted, remove from burner and add gelatin.
Dissolve gelatin and cool mixture until it is congealed slightly.
Soften the cream cheese with some of the pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Whip gelatin mixture.
Add pineapple-cheese mixture to gelatin and then fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Cook noodles.
Mix soups and milk. Add to noodles.
Add sausage.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Cook in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Cream cheeses together.
Add sour cream, eggs (1 at a time), sugar, lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch, flour and butter.
Beat about 15 minutes.
Pour into greased spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Turn off heat and let cake stand in oven with door open 2 hours.
Remove and refrigerate once cake is at room temperature. Gently loosen, but do not remove side of pan until cake has been chilled.
Top with strawberries, arranged pointed end up.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Spread in deep dish.
Sprinkle salt, garlic salt and chili powder on meat.
Add grated cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick 1 minute by hand.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: rib or chicken marinade
directions: Mix dressing, vinegar and sauce together in a large bowl.
Put in chicken and mix with sauce so each piece is dipped in sauce. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Put directly on grill or in oven the next day.

title: short ribs
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup water and cover; simmer in Dutch oven about 2 hours.
Add more water during cooking, if pot is dry.
Combine barbecue sauce, pineapple preserves and vinegar in a bowl and pour over ribs.
Cook 20 minutes more or until meat is tender.
Serve with medium broad noodles.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add wild strawberry Jell-O.
Let cool.
Freeze.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; combine sugar, shortening and salt. Cool to lukewarm; add 1 cup flour and mix well.
Add softened yeast and egg and remaining flour.
Knead until dough is satiny, smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise in warm place 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; let rise 30 minutes.
Turn out on lightly greased board and shape into desired shape.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: birthday fun cups
directions: Microwave margarine and marshmallows at high for 2 minutes. Stir. Microwave 1 minute longer. Stir until smooth.

Add cereal. Stir until well coated. Divide warm mixture into 24 muffin pan cups coated with vegetable spray. Shape into cups. Cool. Fill with your favorite frozen yogurt or ice cream. Sprinkle with colored party sprinkles or small candies. Serve immediately or keep in freezer.

title: pepperoni zucchini casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine zucchini, onion, cheeses, pepperoni and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
In another bowl combine oil, eggs and Bisquick.
Mix well.
Add to the zucchini mixture and blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture in a baking dish.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until cheese starts browning.

title: italian chicken with vegetables(microwave)
directions: Lay 2 sets.
Arrange 1/2 of vegetables in center of each container.
Top evenly with chicken strips.
Sprinkle evenly with Italian dressing, seasonings and water.
Cover.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage.
Mix with grated cheese and Bisquick.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: brenda's fried quail
directions: Wash quail and pat dry with a paper towel.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Beat egg.
Add 1 cup of milk to egg.
Roll quail in flour, then in milk and egg mixture, then in flour again, coating generously.
Cook in frypan with 1 inch of oil, waiting until the oil gets hot before putting the quail in the pan.
Brown evenly on all sides.
Cook on simmer for 15 to 20 minutes for tenderness. Allow 1 quail per person, split in half for faster cooking or can be left whole.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup and add hot water.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
In a large bowl, add margarine, corn, half of cheese, soup and rice; toss, being careful not to break up rice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into baking dish; place in oven.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle some cheese on top; place back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple vanilla dessert
directions: Spread on top of pudding.
Garnish with almonds and maraschino cherries.

title: steak sauce
directions: Mix well and let steaks soak in sauce overnight.
Mmm, how good they will taste.

title: pot roast
directions: Use roaster pan. Add all ingredients and bake in oven at 275° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pineapple bar cake
directions: In mixing bowl, put melted margarine.
Add sugar and well beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients which pecans have been added to.
Add pineapple to creamed mixture, then the dry ingredients. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Freezes good!

title: lamb chops with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: In a food processor, cream butter with tomatoes and pepper. Refrigerate.
Season lamb chops and broil, turning once, about 8 minutes.
They should be slightly pink inside.
Top with 1 tablespoon of butter and a sprig of parsley.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine egg, milk and shortening and add all at once to flour mixture. Stir until dry ingredients are moist but still lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix cornbread as directed.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken breasts in beaten eggs and then in crumb mixture.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn over and bake another 20 minutes or until tender and done through.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, cinnamon, fruits and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In blender, puree tomatoes until smooth.
Should have 2 cups.
Soak raisins in boiling water. Cool.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, tomato pulp and raisins and soaking water.
Beat well.

title: mushroom business
directions: Chop and saute mushrooms with 2 Tbsp. butter for 1-2 minutes. Butter 3 slices of bread and cut into 1-inch squares.
Place in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine mushrooms with onion, celery, green pepper, mayonnaise, salt, and pepper. Spread mixture over bread cubes.
Butter and cube 3 more slices of bread, spread over mushrooms.
Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate.
One hour before baking, spoon mushroom soup over the top.
Cube and butter remaining 2 slices of bread. Sprinkle over the top.
Refrigerate 1 hour more.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle with cheese 10 minutes before it is done.
Serves 8-10.

title: grandma's swiss green bean casserole
directions: Combine butter and flour together over medium heat.
Cook green beans.
Combine everything but cheese and melted butter. Put in casserole dish and top with cheese and melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Combine.
Do not overbeat or use high mix speed (will cause air bubbles).

title: mother's rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; stir in egg, lemon rind and juice and water.
Cook over boiling water until slightly thickened.
Pour over rhubarb in pie shell.
Top with a lattice crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes a 2 crust 9-inch pie.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, margarine, nuts, extract and 1 egg. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan that is lightly greased.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: strawberry short pie
directions: Buy or make crust.
Whip the cream and sugar until soft peaks form; set aside.
Pour milk into mixing bowl.
Add pudding and beat with rotary beater until well blended, about 1 minute. Immediately fold whipped cream and strawberries into pudding. Pour in pie shell.
Chill until firm.
If desired, garnish with whole strawberries.

title: snowball icebox cake
directions: Mix jello with cold water.
Add boiling water, sugar, pineapple juice and all.
Refrigerate until partly firm.
Whip 2 packages of Dream Whip until firm.
Fold into jello mixture.
Line mixing bowl (2 quart size) with waxed paper.
Pinch angel food cake into small pieces.
Arrange in bowl by adding a layer of cake and a layer of jello until all is used.
Chill overnight. Unmold and frost with third box of Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and keep in refrigerator.

title: foolproof yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add salt.
Scald milk and let cool to lukewarm.
Add milk to mixture, then add yeast.
Mix flour until it becomes a soft dough.
Cover and let ripen 3 hours.
Knead and make into rolls.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake until light brown at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place one layer of potatoes (thinly sliced) into a pan. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Add 1/2 of the celery, chopped onion and chopped green bell pepper.
Add another layer of potatoes and top with the remaining 1/2 celery, onions and green pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Place strips of cheese on top of other ingredients.
Mix about 3 tablespoons cornstarch with one cup milk and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: calypso coleslaw
directions: In large bowl combine cabbage, onions, cheese, olives and corn. Combine mayonnaise, sugar, mustard, celery seed and vinegar.
Mix well, pour over cabbage mixture and toss to coat.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: baked party cheese
directions: Divide sliced almonds in half.
Use half in recipe and half on top for garnish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle reserved almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in a small casserole dish until bubbly.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: shrimp or surami dip
directions: Place all ingredients, except shrimp or surami, in small mixer bowl.
Mix very well.
Then add shrimp or surami and mix well again.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Take yellow cake mix.
Cut in 1 stick or margarine.
Add 1 egg, well beaten.
Mix together.
Reserve 1 cup for topping. Press the rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the pumpkin over cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except corn flakes.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is a nice change from baked potatoes to serve with steaks.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread 1 teaspoon on assorted crackers.

title: chomboloto "italian coffee cake"
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, lemon rind, lemon juice, annisette and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: chicken parisianne
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Best served with rice as side dish.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Fry stems and sausage, crumbling the meat as it cooks.
Add crumbs and water, mixing well.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake white cake as directed on box.
While cake is
hot, punch holes in the cake.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
After cake is completely cool, spread whipped topping over the top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: fast fixing fruit cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, oil, eggs and milk until smooth and well mixed.
Dice the apple pie filling and fold into cake mixture.
Pour into lightly-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
You can sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: venison meatballs
directions: Mix together ground deer meat, dried onion soup mix, egg, 1 tablespoon of Worcestershire sauce, rolled oats, dried parsley flakes, milk and catsup.
Form into walnut size balls and set aside.
In a 10 x 10-inch square microwave-safe casserole, mix the beef broth and 1 tablespoon of Worcestershire sauce.
Add meatballs.
Cook, covered on 70 (Roast) for 10 minutes.

title: ground nut stew
directions: Cook chicken in salt, bouillon and pepper.
Save broth.
Melt butter and saute onion; add flour.
Gradually add broth and stir until a soupy consistency.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
(If too thick, add cold milk.)
Season with curry; add chicken and heat.
Serve over rice.
Add any of the following. Mix together and enjoy.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together the chicken, soup and picante.
Taste for personal preference.
Add more picante or Tabasco, etc.
Dip flour tortilla in picante sauce, tomato juice, chicken broth or oil to soften.
Fill with several spoonfuls of chicken sauce.

title: chocolate cherry thumbprints
directions: Beat sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 cup morsels, melted.
Mix well. Stir in oats, flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Cover and chill dough 1 hour.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Put all ingredients in pan.
Bring to boil, stirring all the time.
Cool 9-inch baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate.

title: ham-egg brunch
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour mixture over bread, ham and cheese.
Cover.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
In the morning, cover with crushed cornflakes and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice pickles very thin.
Mix pickles with peppers, onions and salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Stir together sugar, celery seed, vinegar and mustard seed until sugar is dissolved. Pour over pickles and place in freezer containers.
Freeze.
If refrigerated, pickles will keep 2 to 3 weeks.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch deep pie plate and spread softened cream cheese over bottom of dish.
Mix chili and salsa together and pour over cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 25 to 35 minutes until bubbly and melted.
Serve hot with your favorite chips.

title: tacos
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Stir in chili powder, salt, garlic powder and tomato sauce.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Heat taco shells in oven at 250° for 5 minutes.
Assemble tacos by layering meat, cheese, lettuce and tomatoes in each shell.
Serve with taco sauce; top with sour cream.
Makes 10 tacos.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute celery in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients except cornflakes and almonds.
Sprinkle them on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 8 to 10.

title: grinder sauce(fast and easy)
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter. Add the onions and peppers.
Cook until almost done.
In a separate skillet, brown the hamburg until well done.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes. Add onions and peppers.
Add the tomato sauce, hot pepper and garlic powder.
Cook for 20 minutes. Spoon in grinder rolls and enjoy.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until it does not jiggle in center.

title: mom's extra special broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Place in a glass baking dish. Mix together the mayonnaise, soup, milk and lemon juice. Mix well and pour over the broccoli. Top with cheese slices. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in 1/2 cup shortening.
Mixture should resemble coarse meal.
Blend in vanilla, egg and milk. Mixture should form a ball.
Roll on floured board; cut with cutters and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Use only shortening in this recipe for best results.
This is a cookie batter that does not need to be refrigerated.

title: meat sauce(for your favorite pasta)
directions: Crumble ground meat; cook until done, but not brown.
Saute vegetables until done, but not brown.
Add to meat.
Add tomato sauce, spicy sauce and 1 (10-ounce) can of water.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir several times to keep from sticking.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions and save; cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove from pan; drain off all but about 4 tablespoons bacon drippings and then saute onions and peppers until tender.
Add crushed tomatoes, bay leaves and sugar; simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chopped broccoli; drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, butter, eggs and onions. Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle cheese on top. Sprinkle crackers on top of cheese. Press lightly with hands. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand 20 minutes.

title: baked beans(servings: 12)
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and reserve.
Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Drain.
Pour into large bowl and add remaining ingredients, adding bacon into mixture last.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: meat loaf for 50 to 70
directions: Put in large pan and mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 3 large pans and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
You may need to cover them halfway through so they will not get too brown. Grease the pan you are baking the meat loaf in (pans 12 x 17 x 2-inches).

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Prepare recipe for Bisquick drop biscuits.
Add Cheddar cheese to taste.
Dip ice cream scoop (drop in pan).
Let rise 7 to 10 minutes; very important. Cook 7 to 10 minutes at 400°. Brush with melted butter mixed with garlic powder and parsley.

title: marlsgate chicken salad
directions: Season chicken breast.
Grill.
Cool and cube.
Add mayonnaise, sandwich spread, grapes and almonds.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: In a medium size pan or casserole dish, pour soups and water; mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over soups; do not stir in.
Lay cut up chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover; do not remove cover while baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven; let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: speedy chicken and shrimp
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onion and pineapple in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in chicken ala king, shrimp and lemon juice; heat through.
Serve on rice; sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked meat pies
directions: Combine ground chuck, sausage, onions and seasoning in a large pan; cook over medium heat, stirring often until meat loses its red color.
Do not overcook the meat.
Sprinkle the flour over the meat mixture, stirring often, until well combined with meat. Remove from heat.
Place meat in a large colander placed in a pie plate or dish to drain off excess grease and juice.
This may take several hours.
Place 2 tablespoons of mixture in center of egg roll wrapper diagonally.
Beat 1 egg.
With fingers, spread beaten egg on 2 side corners.
Fold over corners to the middle.
Spread beaten egg over the 2 sides.
Fold 2 side corners to center. Seal.
Roll into neat package and seal tightly.
Place on a cookie sheet which has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Place meat pies seam side down.
Spray the tops with vegetable cooking spray.

title: tabouleh
directions: Place cracked wheat in a bowl and cover with cold water.
Let soak 30 minutes.
Drain and press out moisture.
Spread out on clean cloth and allow to dry.
Wash parsley.
Cut off stalks.
Wrap in towel and refrigerate.
Put wheat in mixing bowl and add onions. Mix it well (using your hands is the best way to be sure it is well mixed).
Add parsley and mint.
Beat olive oil with lemon juice and stir in salt and pepper.
Add to salad and toss well.
Peel, seed and dice tomatoes.
Gently stir into salad.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Very good served with pita bread.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 400°; cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Spread over pretzel crust; refrigerate 10 minutes.
Mix strawberry jello, boiling water and frozen strawberries.
Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into small cubes. Roll in flour, salt and pepper; brown in hot butter. Add 1/2 cup water and vinegar; simmer until tender. Add water as necessary to keep from burning. When tender, pour off excess liquid. Add remaining ingredients. Cover; simmer until everything is heated through. Don't boil. Serve over brown rice or noodles.

title: peach angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed, baking in a tube pan.
When cool, cut cake horizontally in 3 even layers.
Whip cream until it stands in peaks.
Spread part of cream on one layer and top with peaches.
Repeat on each layer, stacking one on top of the other. Spread remaining cream on top.
Top with peaches.
Serve immediately.
To prevent peaches from browning, dissolve 1 teaspoon ascorbic acid crystals in 3 tablespoons water and mix well.

title: caribbean fruit salad
directions: Toss together; cover and chill for 2 hours.
Yields 20 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a deep heavy saucepan.
Remove bacon bits and drain on paper toweling.
Pour off fat.
Measure 2 tablespoons and return to saucepan.
Add onions and cook until transparent, but not brown.
Add raw potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat just to boiling. Season to taste.
Yields 6 cups.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Combine sweet potato, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon. Shape a small amount around each marshmallow. Roll in crumbs. Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes or until lightly puffed (do not overbake or marshmallows will melt).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In large frypan, saute onions with vegetable oil until transparent.
Add chicken and cream cheese (break up with spoon). Cook until melted.
Stir in chili powder, garlic powder, cumin and 3/4 cup Colby and 3/4 cup Monterey Jack cheeses.
Add half jar of salsa.
Stir until bubbling.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of 2 large baking pans with Pam.
Lay flour tortilla in pan.
Add 1/3 cup mixture and roll up.
Arrange seam side down.
Add remaining salsa on top and sprinkle remaining cheeses on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nutty cheese ball
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese; chop onions, green pepper and celery. Mix all ingredients except pecans until smooth.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Store covered in refrigerator no longer than 2 weeks.
Serve at room temperature for best flavor.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and stir in M&M's.
Bake at 350°.

title: colorado joe's spaghetti seasoning
directions: Buy all jars the same size and mix all together.
Store in airtight container.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons to your own homemade spaghetti sauce.

title: molasses krinkles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls and dip into sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruitcake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease 10 x 15 inch jelly roll pan. Combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend in dry ingredients.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Spread batter evenly.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool. Makes about 4 dozen bars.

title: antipasto salad platter
directions: Pour Italian dressing over pepperoni, beans, tomatoes, cucumber and mushrooms.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Drain, reserving marinade.

title: nun's cake
directions: Mix chocolate chips, pecans and coconut with flour; set aside. Put all other ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat together on medium speed until well blended.
Fold in chips, nuts and coconut. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend the ingredients, except cheese.
Split rolls and spread ham mixture on bottoms.
Top with cheese.
Place the tops on the rolls.
Cover tightly with foil.
Heat in 400° oven until hot and cheese melts.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add sugar, egg, butter and vanilla.
Beat smooth and stir in nuts.
Put in greased 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until top is lightly brown and springs back.
Remove from oven and arrange marshmallows, nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Put back in oven until chocolate has melted.
Swirl over marshmallows.
Cool until chocolate has set. Cut into squares.

title: zucchini casserole with meat
directions: Boil zucchini in 1 1/2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
