Brown beef in skillet. Drain zucchini and mix with 1/2 teaspoon salt and rest of ingredients, except half of the grated cheese to save for top of casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Using a glass 8

x 13 casserole, spread refried beans. Mix sour cream in medium bowl with taco seasoning, then spread over refried beans. Next, spread on guacamole. Sprinkle on onions. Next, sprinkle on cheese, followed by tomato and black olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vanilla cream topping
directions: Stir together until smooth.

title: devilicious eggs
directions: Slice
eggs
in
halves
lengthwise, remove yolks.
Mash yolks with
a
fork,
add
mayonnaise, pecans, onion, vinegar, mustard, salt and parsley, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into egg whites. Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; cool, then dice into cubes (can leave skins on if desired).
Set aside.
Fry bacon in a large frying pan.
Remove bacon, but save grease.
Saute onion (chopped) in bacon grease. When onion is soft, add salt, pepper and celery seed.
Mix constantly.
Re-add the bacon and potatoes (bacon must be broken up into bits).
Add vinegar.
Still mix constantly, then add egg. Serve hot.

title: holiday slaw
directions: Gradually blend dressing into mayonnaise.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add dressing mixture and toss lightly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into Pyrex casserole dish. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Let sit out 1 hour before refrigeration to let the hot pasta absorb the dressing and spice flavors.
Black olives, broccoli, cauliflower or any vegetable may be added.
Chill well.

title: taco pie
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and stir in taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Unroll crescent rolls and press onto the bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan (prepared with nonstick spray) to form a crust.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup of crushed taco chips and spread seasoned beef mixture over chips.

title: basic buttermilk bran muffins
directions: Combine the flour, bran, salt and baking soda in a large bowl. Beat together the buttermilk, egg whites, molasses and butter. Add liquid mixture to the dry ingredients.
Stir together only enough to moisten.
Fold in apple and choice of other ingredients (no more than total of 2 cups).
Fill 24 greased muffin tins. Bake about 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put into a greased pan.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard together, then add carrots, onion and pepper.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly brown meat; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add seasoning, beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put creamed potatoes in mounds over top of meat and sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: knock you nakeds
directions: Combine and mix well cake mix, nuts, 1/3 cup milk and butter. Press half of this mixture into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Melt caramel candies in top of a double boiler with 1/2 cup milk. When caramel mixture is well mixed, pour over baked mixture. Cover with chocolate chips and pour the rest of dough on top of chips. Bake for 18 minutes at 350°. Cool before slicing. Yield: 20 servings.

title: chicken savannah
directions: Soak chicken in buttermilk for 1 1/2 hours; remove and drain. Mix flour, salt, pepper and garlic.
Thoroughly coat chicken with mixture and allow to sit for 20 minutes.
Heat vegetable oil to 375° and fry chicken.

title: oven-barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in a greased roasting pan.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Drain ribs.

title: red baked spanish onions
directions: Peel and cut onions in half.
Place cut side down in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn onions cut side up.
Combine other ingredients. Spoon half of mixture over onions.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle the remainder of mixture over onions.
Baste with liquid in pan and continue baking until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: tater tot bake
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add taco mix, chives and mushroom soup, then put in baking dish.
Add the Tater Tots on the top; cook until golden brown.
Add cheese until melted.
Bake the dish at 350°.

title: butter bundt coffee cake
directions: To the yellow cake mix, add the eggs, pudding, oil, water and butter flavoring.
Mix for 8 minutes.
Mix together the sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Layer cake mixture and sugar mixture in Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.
After cool, drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: creamy whipped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
Heat potatoes, 1 teaspoon salt and enough water to cover to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain well.

title: birthday cake
directions: Mix with hands, put in pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the sugar, Karo and water until it boils all over bottom of boiler.
Put peanuts in with this mixture.
Cook until syrup turns honey colored.
Take off fire; stir in soda.
Stir and pour into a buttered pan.
When it has hardened, break into pieces.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce in flat pan.
Sprinkle over the top onion, celery, green pepper and chestnuts (in layers).
Break peas apart and sprinkle over while frozen.
Spread mayonnaise like frosting over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and Parmesan cheese to completely cover top.
Sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Decorate with tomatoes and eggs.
Refrigerate a few hours to blend flavors.
Keeps 3 to 4 days.

title: green bean thyme
directions: Cover husked corn with cold water, adding 1 teaspoon sugar per dozen ears. Bring to a boil and boil hard for 3 minutes.
Turn off heat. Cover pot and let corn stay until wanted; the longer, the better.

title: jello cake
directions: Combine cake mix, jello, oil and 1/2 water. Mix well. Add remaining water and eggs (one at a time). Mix well after each egg. Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Let cool completely before turning out.

title: red potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Cut into chunks.
Combine potatoes and red pepper in a large bowl; stir in Watercress Mayonnaise.
Place on a bed of watercress, and arrange tomato wedges around salad.
Yields 9 cups.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Peel and dice turnips.
Cook in salt water.
Drain and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Brown ham in margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually while stirring ham mixture. Cook until thickened.
Stir in soup.
Pour sauce over turnips and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon and soda; set aside.
In another bowl, stir shortening and sugars until combined.
Stir in egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in spiced flour mixture; mix. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Flatten each ball by crisscrossing with a fork.
Bake in 375° oven 6 to 8 minutes until edges are brown.
Remove and cool on rack.
Makes 36 cookies.
Serve with Coffee Floats.

title: corn dogs
directions: **Best to warm hot dogs to room temperature before cooking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the oil, eggs and sugar.
Stir in vanilla and zucchini. Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours in greased loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot pickles
directions: Mix sugar and cayenne pepper together.
Layer pickles and sugar mixture in jar. Refrigerate for approximately 2 weeks before serving.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine together.
Add sugar slowly, then milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
(Great on top of brownies.)

title: rich coffee cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, during beating.
Add vanilla, then flour and milk, alternately.
Put half in greased square pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and lots of cinnamon. Add rest of batter and sprinkle with sugar and lots of cinnamon again.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: voodoo chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, soy sauce, onion, garlic and pepper. Marinate chicken at least 3 hours in refrigerator; drain.
Save marinade for later.
Mix mustard and 4 tablespoons ketchup.
Brush each piece of chicken with mustard mixture, coating well.
Bake, skin side down, at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Bake on foil sprayed with Pam.)
Turn pieces.
Mix remaining ketchup with milk and reserved marinade.
Pour sauce over chicken; bake additional 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Combine and heat thoroughly.
Serve in soup bowls topped with shredded cheese and bacon bits.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and eggs; blend well.
Stir in cheese, bell pepper, hot sauce, oil, corn and onion.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: raisin apple crisp
directions: Go to the store.
Buy something you can make in the microwave. Make sure it doesn't take more than 7 minutes to cook.
If you have company, be sure to dispose of the package before they see it.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetables, fish or shrimp batter
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
in
a jar and then add water and shake. Batter should be consistency of pancake batter.

title: sophia's cinnamon buns
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and set side.
In saucepan, heat milk until skin forms.
Pour hot milk over butter and sugar mixture; stir. Add 1 cup of flour to butter mixture and stir together.
Add yeast once it has bubbled.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Add eggs, and beat.
Add another cup of flour; mix into dough until elastic looking and dry.
Let raise in covered, greased bowl, until doubled (2 to 3 hours) and then turn.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook rice according to directions on box; drain.
Mix with the hamburger and onion.
Also add remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grape crumb pie
directions: Separate grapes and grind the skins.
Add sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt.
Mix and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly and combine with sugar.
Add vegetable oil and mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Sift.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well; add vanilla, nuts and apples and mix.
Batter will be on the stiff side.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
May be topped with powdered sugar or glaze.

title: texas hash
directions: Combine ground beef, onions and green pepper and brown in hot fat.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Turn into covered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: saucy louisiana chicken
directions: In a large skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Add green peppers and chicken.
Cook 5 minutes until chicken is cooked.
Blend tomatoes, cornstarch and cayenne.
Add to skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened; add green beans or mushrooms or both and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: easy ice cream cake
directions: Use a Pyrex dish and line the bottom of the pan with ice cream sandwiches.
You may have to cut some sandwiches in half to cover the entire bottom depending on size of dish.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip to fill in the cracks.
Place another layer of ice cream sandwiches on top of the Cool Whip.
Then spread another layer of Cool Whip on top of those sandwiches.
Finish it off with crushed Oreo cookies.
Freeze for a short time and then serve.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix as given; pour into 9 x 13 pan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread mix according to package directions and bake. Cool (better if made several hours or night before using). Crumble and add green pepper, onions, corn and mayonnaise; mix well.

title: sachertort cookies
directions: Beat the oleo and pudding until light and fluffy.
Beat in the egg.
Gradually add the flour. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. With thumb, make imprint in center of each cookie. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, fill each imprint with jelly or jam. In small pan over low heat, melt 1 cup chocolate chips in 6 tablespoons oleo.
Frost tops.
Yields 48 to 50 cookies.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Chill. Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix well the meat, crumbs, eggs, milk, onion, Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt, pepper and oregano.
Shape into two loaves.
Put into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Pour pizza sauce over.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over sauce.
Bake until melted.
Could be wrapped in foil and baked on grill.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler.
Cook until smooth. Spread in buttered pan.

title: jeff's dip
directions: Cook ground beef and drain fat.
Add taco mix.
Remove from heat.
Set aside.
In a microwave dish or in the top of a double boiler, add cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes and chilies.
Melt cheese, stirring so it doesn't burn.
Add ground beef. Mix well.
Serve with corn chips.

title: dream cake
directions: Blend cake mix with Dream Whip topping.
Mix eggs and cold water in bowl.
Blend all ingredients together with electric mixer until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken and vegetable rice
directions: Cook chicken in water until it falls off bones.
Remove the bones.
Add salt, rice, lemon and pan drippings to chicken and broth.
Bring to boil; stir well and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Remove from heat; add parsley and celery.
Toss lightly with fork.
Makes 9 servings.
You may also cook the rice and other ingredients in water and substitute tuna.

title: brownies (cake type)
directions: Mix ingredients well, then stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: easy cheese soup
directions: Mix and simmer first 7 ingredients for 10 minutes until tender. Do NOT drain water.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3 or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Freeze in small airtight containers.
To serve, remove from freezer and let thaw about 10 minutes.
Scoop or scrape into stemmed glasses.
Serve with straws if desired.
Makes 14 (6 ounce) servings.

title: orange carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add carrots, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.
(Press down a little when dropped on cookie sheet.)

title: sweet kosher dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place pickle slices in a bowl.
Cover with 2 cups sugar and 1 tablespoon vinegar; stir well.
Let set until it makes its own syrup, stirring occasionally until all sugar is dissolved.
Pack pickles back in jar, add small amount of pickling spice or cinnamon stick and whole spice.
Place several onion slices on top and place lid on.
Refrigerate 4 days before using.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients together. Put 1/3 cup mixture in mug and fill with boiling water. Stir. Makes nice gift, also. Put mixture in pretty container with directions on how to make.

title: sharon squares
directions: Flatten dinner rolls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise and spread over crust.
Top with shredded celery and carrots.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Spread cream cheese over bottom of glass pie dish or square pyrex dish.
Then layer chili and cheese.
Microwave 4-5 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with green onion and dollops of sour cream if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, 10x sugar, 1 cup chopped nuts and cocoa. Add syrup and rum; mix well.
Make 1-inch balls and roll in 1/2 cup of sugar and remainder of nuts.
Store in airtight container.

title: sauce for barbecue chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vinegar, egg and oil.
Coat chicken. Cook for 1 1/2 hours on grill.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal lunchbox cookies
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add peanut butter and eggs.
Add 1/4 cup milk and flour sifted with cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir in raisins.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together until smooth.
Pour onto floured cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
The pumpkin bars will have a cake like texture but are moist.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and sugar together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Be careful to make sure it's even and that it's all covered.
Mix jello with water until dissolved.
Mix in strawberries and pineapple.
Let partially set.
Pour over cream cheese.
Let cool.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly french toast(breakfast)
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, sugar and cinnamon together in bowl.
Make three peanut butter sandwiches.
Dip sandwiches into batter; both sides.
Fry in pan with butter until brown, then turn and fry other side.
Serve with milk, eat with knife and fork; no need for syrup.
Kids love it!

title: aunt peggy's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and salt in heavy skillet until mixture spins a thread.
Leave on heat and add peanuts.
Leave on high heat, stirring constantly, until peanuts are parched-looking (tan) and syrup is red.

title: pork chop and vegetable skillet
directions: Trim fat from chops.
In a 12-inch skillet, cook chops over medium-high heat in hot oil, 4 to 5 minutes per side.
Remove chops.
Add onions to skillet; cook until tender.
Drain fat, if necessary.
Add undrained tomatoes, water, paprika, garlic salt and caraway seed.
Return chops to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and green pepper. Cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until pork and potatoes are tender.
Serve immediately.

title: savory mustard mold
directions: Soften gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water; stir over low heat to dissolve.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard, salt and paprika, then add to gelatine.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in sour (or whipped) cream.
Fill a 3-cup mold and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in bread pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add hot water. Add flour mixed with soda.
Add chopped nuts, oatmeal and vanilla, then 8 ounces butterscotch nibs.
Bake teaspoonfuls on sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: anchovies au gratin
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Peel potatoes and cut into lengthwise strips.
Butter baking dish, then add potatoes, onions and anchovy fillets, finishing with a layer of potatoes. Pour in a little juice from anchovy jar and dot with remaining butter.
Bake in moderate oven (400°), adding 1/2 of cream after 10 minutes.
Add remaining cream after another 10 minutes.
After 30 minutes, reduce heat to 300° and bake another 30 minutes. Casserole is ready when potatoes are soft.
Serve immediately.

title: beef bourguignon(beef burgundy)
directions: Dredge beef cubes in flour and brown in oil.
Remove meat and wipe Dutch oven clean.
Return meat to Dutch oven and add carrot, onion, garlic, thyme, bay leaf, catsup, beef stock and red wine. Put Dutch oven in oven and bake at 325° for about 3 hours.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In small pan, mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, vinegar and pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat.
Stir until thick (takes quite awhile).
Cool.
Pour over apples and pineapple.
Add 1 cup of peanuts and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with remaining nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: almond covered pretzels
directions: Put 1 cube of almond bark in small bowl.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Dip pretzels into almond bark until covered well.
Put on wax paper to harden.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add margarine and mix.
Add pintos, coconut and pecans; mix well. Make two 9-inch deep dish pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's zucchini
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in sugar, flour and pepper.
Add squash and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until squash is fork-tender.

title: swiss loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving some of the cheese to spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour grease off the top and serve.

title: rose's caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat, cool until mix begins to thicken; then add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Very good on Black Walnut Cake.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
water.
stir
in
sugar.
Add egg, butter or
margarine
and
flour.
Beat with mixer until well mixed. Fill greased and heated muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 450°
for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Dough keeps well in refrigerator 4 to 5 days.

title: fritter batter
directions: Can add chopped cooked shrimp or ham or corn.

title: christening punch
directions: Mix water with fruit juices before serving.
Add to sherbet and ice cream.
Makes about 65 cups.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir into stuffing.
Divide and place half of stuffing mixture over bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour into dish and cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients in a double boiler.
Cook until thick. Pour into cooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and cool. Cream the butter and sugar and add egg. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix all together and add 1/2 cup nutmeats.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Mix the rest of the ingredients. (Dough should be firm, not dry.)
Add extra water by tablespoons if mixture is too dry.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water slowly 15 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 325° about 45 minutes.
Make a double cake.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop pepper and onion.
Mix together and set aside.
Grate both cheeses.
Mix together and set aside. Heat enchilada sauce in saucepan.
Melt shortening in frying pan. Dip each tortilla shell in hot shortening for 1 to 2 seconds on each side to soften shell.
Stack hot shell on plate with paper towel.
Coat bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with half of heated enchilada sauce.
Save remaining sauce for later.
Place cheese mixture and small amount of pepper and onion on one end of shell. Roll entire mixture tightly in shell.
Place roll, seam side down, in pan.
Repeat until all shells are used.
Sprinkle remaining cheese, peppers and onions over shells.
Pour remaining sauce over the shells.
Heat in oven for 10 minutes or until sauce bubbles.

title: quick dessert
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract. Stir in the flour and baking powder; mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spoon pie filling into the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place bottom side up on serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar and spoon whipped cream over each serving.
This is great served warm.

title: marinade for steak
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Marinate steaks for at least 4 hours before cooking.

title: easy corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, oil and egg, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown and wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Yields 9 servings.

title: pineapple cake filling
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour, pineapple and butter. Mix and cook, stirring constantly until thick. Pour into a bowl to cool. Add butter. "Ice" cake with this. Use a Pillsbury Plus cake mix. Cut the layer into to make 4 layers.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar;
add
egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon,	apple pie spice, baking soda, baking powder and
salt together.
Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add chopped
nuts and raisins.	Bake in well buttered cake pans
for
40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: strawberry kiwi pizza
directions: Mix flour, pecan chips and butter and put in pizza pan.
Cook on 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip (save about 1 cup Cool Whip) until smooth and put on top of cooled cake.
Add sliced strawberries to cover pizza.
Cover with strawberry glaze.
Decorate with kiwi.
Dot top of pizza with leftover Cool Whip.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix in the graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top followed by coconut, then the nuts.
Pour condensed milk over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: gingerbread christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 1 hour.
(I often leave them overnight.)
Roll dough out about 1/8-inch thick. (You will need to work in more flour.) Cut in desired shapes. Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
(Can be doubled or tripled easily, freezes very well!)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spray casserole
dish with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon-blueberry oat muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine the egg white, egg, milk, butter, lemon peel, and vanilla. Mix well.
Add to dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in berries.
Coat muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray or use paper liners.
Fill 2/3 full with batter.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Chop onion and saute in margarine until soft.
Add chicken and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Remove chicken from pan and add flour and salt until all lumps are gone.
Add the broth, stirring at all times.
Cook until it thickens.
Add paprika and sour cream. Stir.
Add chicken and spoon sauce over all.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in double boiler. Bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cook until mixture melts, stirring constantly. Spread in waxed paper lined pan.
Pour semi-sweet chocolate over top and swirl with knife to marbleize. Chill until firm.
Cut into desired size. Refrigerate.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Mix liver, bread crumbs, egg, flour, salt, pepper and onion. Drop one teaspoon of mixture at a time into boiling salt water. Boil 15 minutes.
Remove dumplings to serving dish.
Brown bread crumbs in butter and use as topping.

title: butterfly salad
directions: Cut slices of pineapple in half; arrange on lettuce leaf with half slice of banana in center.
On each piece of pineapple, arrange 2 or 3 cherries.
This will make an effective and pretty butterfly.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: tahitian curried shrimp
directions: Saute onions in butter until yellow.
Add shrimp, garlic and curry.
Stir well.
Add sherry.
Cover and cook over very low heat 15 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with wild rice and soy sauce.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine 1/4 cup oleo, soup, sour cream, cheese, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix.
Add potatoes.
Combine other 1/4 cup oleo with crushed corn flakes.
Spread on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spanish beans
directions: Pour all ingredients together in a pot.
Cook for 45 minutes on medium heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain fat.
Add meat; cook for 2 minutes.
Add rice.
Add egg to meat and rice.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Serves 4.

title: torte
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar about 20 minutes.
Add melted and cooled chocolate.
Slowly fold in flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in slowly.
Pour into greased and floured 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Take cakes out of pans and cool.
Cut in half horizontally.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Pour chopped nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Add butter, corn, salt and milk.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: italian sausage pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan. Brown sausage, onion and green pepper; cook until vegetables are just tender.
Drain.
Stir in mushrooms.
Remove from heat.
In small saucepan, heat 1/2 cup tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water for topping.
In large bowl, dissolve yeast from hot roll mix in warm tomato sauce and water.
Stir in hot roll mix flour mixture; blend well.
With greased fingers, press out dough in prepared pan, forming rim around edge.
Spread reserved tomato sauce over dough; sprinkle with cheese.
Layer prepared sausage and vegetable mixture over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour over browned meat.
Bake in covered pan until last 15 minutes, then remove lid.

title: helen's famous chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, place chicken covered with water.
Bring to a boil; boil gently for about 3/4 hour.
Remove chicken breasts from water.
Cool and remove skin.
Break chicken in pieces and set aside; add optional seasonings.
Add a cup of hot water.
Continue cooking and add carrots, thinly sliced, and rice.
Cook slowly until carrots are done.
Adjust for flavor with bouillon cubes; begin with 2, but not more than 6.
Add chicken pieces.
Heat well.

title: chicken-rice dinner
directions: Flour chicken pieces
and
brown in oil.
Combine rice, salt and pepper	in
a
greased 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with onion.
Add
mushrooms and juice.
Arrange chicken on top of rice; add
bouillon
dissolved
in boiling water.
Dot with butter. Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for one hour. Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Break chicken into bite size pieces.
Stir sour cream and soup together until blended.
Stir in chicken.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Roll chicken mixture into tortillas and lay side by side until pan is full.
Spread the remaining chicken mixture over the tortillas until they're all moist.
Spread plenty of grated cheese over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 335°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, powdered sugar, 2 cups flour and salt.
Mix well with pastry blender until mixture is well blended.
Pat evenly into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in granulated sugar,
flour, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Mix well and spread over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sift powdered sugar over top.
Let cool.
Cut into squares while hot.
If you choose, you can use the following icing.

title: chex party mix recipe
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet at 200°.
Stir in seasoning. Blend well.
Add Chex and pretzels or nuts.
Mix until pieces are coated.
Cover skillet, leaving lid vents open.
Heat at 250° for 15 minutes.
Stir midway.
Cool on absorbent paper (paper towel).

title: cow pies (cookies)
directions: In double boiler, over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Chill until ready to serve.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut out stem ends of peppers, and remove seeds.
Boil peppers 5 minutes in salted water; drain.
Heat fat and cook celery in it until tender.
Mix with rice and cheese; add salt.
Fill pepper cups with the rice mixture; top with crumbs.
Place pepper in a half inch of hot water in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) until peppers are tender and crumbs browned - about 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: fresh fruit deep dish pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread sliced peaches in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Evenly sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and place pats of oleo over peaches (in that order).

Start at one end and place one of the pie crusts over peaches (letting edges of crust hang over edges of baking dish), then using the other crust, start at the other end and repeat, overlapping in the center of pie.
Tuck all the overlapping pie crust to the inside of baking dish, pushing it down to the bottom.
Cut slits in top of crust to vent steam.
Sprinkle top of pie crust lightly with sugar.
(The crust will have a thick part around the edges.)
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna-rice casserole
directions: Add rice to 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 1/4 cup boiling water. Bring to a boil, cover and turn off heat.
Let stand 13 minutes. Mix soups, milk, pepper and tuna.
Combine with rice and frozen peas.
Put in a large shallow baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs, butter, paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle around the edge and crisscross on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onions together.
Sprinkle handful of salt on 1/4 thick layers.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and squeeze out water.
Mix together brown sugar, vinegar and seasonings.
Heat on stove.
Add cucumbers to hot brine.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not boil.
Put into sterilized jars, about 6 pints.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix well and roll out; cut in shapes.
Bake at 250°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 4 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Let set 24 hours; then drain and serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Leave jello dry and mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: stuffed pepper
directions: Mix ingredients and stuff peppers.
Stand upright in small baking dish.
When about half done, pour tomato sauce over pepper and finish cooking.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and drink.
Cook until thick.
Add jello, cool.
Put strawberries in baked pie shell.
Then pour over strawberries the other ingredients after they cool.

title: sloppy joes pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef over medium heat, 8 to 10 minutes, or until no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Pour off drippings.

title: fried fish filets
directions: You will need a deep pan for frying (with a basket), paper towels and matches.

title: mocha nut muffins(this is a low cholesterol recipe)
directions: Blend all of the ingredients with an electric mixer on medium. Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 20 minutes.
Batter may be made ahead and stored, refrigerated, for several days.

title: minty-fudge sauce
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil in a medium saucepan. Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips until smooth. Stir in vanilla. Pour into jar(s). Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in 3 tablespoons sugar, beaten eggs and starter.
Gradually add 4 cups flour and salt.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise until double in size.

title: thin egg pancakes(eggepannekaker)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add milk and other ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fry in butter in a large, heavy frying pan. (Pour in batter and roll pan until it reaches to size of the pan, very thin.)
Turn once.
Fold in halves or fourths; add butter and brown sugar and roll.
Add more milk or a little cream, if necessary, so batter is liquid enough to roll around in pan to proper size.

title: 1st prize apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in loaf pan.
Ice while hot with powdered sugar.
This cake won first prize at Hancock County Fair. My sister lived in that county before residing in California.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Press chopped pecans into 2 pie shells; bake and cool.
Soften 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese.
Blend in 1 pound box 4x powdered sugar.
Prepare 2 envelopes of Dream Whip as directed on package.
Gradually add cheese and sugar mixture after Dream Whip is beaten to stand in peaks.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into baked pecan pie shells.
Spoon chilled blueberry pie filling over pie. One can makes 2 pies.
Chill several hours before eating a very rich pie.

title: potato filling
directions: Peel the potatoes; cut into pieces and cook in salted water. Drain and mash.
Break the bread into pieces and mix with the potatoes.
Heat milk, then beat into potatoes and bread.
Saute onion and celery in butter for 3 minutes.
Add to potatoes with salt and pepper.
Beat with beater until well mixed.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: will's special sauce
directions: In a big pot, cover bottom with olive oil.
Saute diced onion until they look tan.
Add 1/2 inch of water; cover pot and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Tastes best with big macaroni.

title: anne's chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in slow cooker.
Sprinkle dry salad mix over, cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: orange crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
If desired, top each cookie with a pecan half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Makes approximately 4 to 5 dozen.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion and garlic and cook until crisp-tender.
Blend soup, sour cream, mushrooms, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat.
Cook over low heat.
Toss butter and poppy seed with noodles and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: aunt norma's jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool this mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a well-greased (but not floured) large Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool on rack for 10 minutes before removing cake from pan. Dust powdered sugar over the cake.
This cake has taste and feel of a homemade scratch pound cake.

title: e-t (easy-tasty) beans
directions: Mix beans with ginger ale, brown sugar, catsup and onion.
Put in a 2-quart casserole and top with bacon strips.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli cheddar rolls
directions: Let dough thaw until pliable.
(To thaw dough in microwave, wrap in plastic wrap and microwave on Low power for 6 minutes, rotating occasionally.)
On lightly floured board, roll dough out to a 12-inch square.
Combine all remaining ingredients (except butter) in a small bowl.
Spread filling mixture over dough.
Roll up lengthwise tightly in jelly roll fashion.
Pinch dough along edge to seal filling in.
Slice rolls into 8 pieces.
Cut each slice in half again, not cutting all the way through.
Fan out sides to form butterfly-shaped rolls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and brush with melted butter or margarine.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oven baked potato slices
directions: Melt butter in water in microwave.
Add other ingredients. Cut baking potatoes in half.
Slice almost to bottom, but not cutting through to make fan shape.
Pour mixture on top and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Put bread and 1/2 of the cereal in blender and crumb.
Pour bread mixture, rest of cereal and all the other ingredients into a bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into 6 cup nonstick muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chow mein cake
directions: Add ingredients in order listed and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost cake while hot.

title: punch bowl eggnog
directions: Blend together eggs, milk, sugar and salt.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour into bowl or pitcher.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, several hours or overnight. Stir in liquor just before serving.
Sprinkle each serving with nutmeg, if desired.

title: st. cecilia society punch(for years, a closely-guarded secret in charleston, south
directions: Slice lemons thin and cover with brandy.
Allow to steep for 24 hours.

title: golden wedding punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients 15 minutes before serving.
Yield:
48 servings.

title: caramel ring
directions: Grease a Bundt pan; sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan.
Place bread balls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding over dough.
Melt butter, cinnamon and brown sugar; bring to a boil. Stir to simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mix over rolls; let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix everything, except flour and soda, together well.
Then mix the baking soda in together with 1 cup of the flour.
When mixed, add to rest of the flour.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean!

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chips and cheese, place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle chips and cheese over top of mixture.
Bake at 350 F for 40-50 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook first four ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Add parsley, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and white sauce.
Blend well; chill.
Shape into croquettes.
Roll in bread crumbs; dip in slightly beaten egg to which a little water has been added.
Roll again in crumbs.
Fry in deep hot fat for 3 to 5 minutes; drain.

title: heath bar torte
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
In medium bowl, combine crumbs, walnuts and butter.
Spread in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy. Gradually beat in sugar until stiff peaks form.
Spread over crumbs.
Bake 1 hour; cool.

title: hungarian baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet with cover.
Dust chicken with paprika.
Brown chicken over medium heat.
Place cabbage slices on bottom of a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake in 375° oven until tender, about 25 minutes.
Arrange apple and onion over cabbage.
Sprinkle with lemon peel, sugar and caraway seed.
Place chicken pieces on top and continue baking 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more until cheese is melted.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Pour milk over shortening, sugar and salt.
Add cold water.
Add 1 cup flour, egg and yeast.
Beat. Add cornmeal and flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth. Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Punch, cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Shape into rolls and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together in a casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Add salt, pepper, onion, bell pepper, tomatoes, rice and chili powder. Stir well. Get hot. Pour into ungreased baking dish. Cover with Reynolds Wrap. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage upside-down corn bread
directions: Cook sausage, onion and pepper; drain well.
Stir in flour, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add cheese.
Put mixture in long baking dish.
Prepare corn bread mix by directions on box; spread over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can invert onto a plate.
Freezes well.

title: fiesta steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Cover meat with seasoned flour.
Pound to 1/4-inch thickness. Brown in oil in large skillet.
Pour off oil.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add to meat.
Add onions.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 1 hour.
Add green pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and continue cooking slowly 25 minutes or until meat is tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cut out the core in cabbage.
Steam cabbage in boiling water just until leaves are wilted.
Remove from water and separate leaves.
In big pot, mix soup, water and sauerkraut; bring to boil.
Then turn it down to a slow boil.
Mix ground beef, rice, onion, garlic, pepper, salt and 2 eggs together.
Put about 1/2 cup of meat mixture on leaf of cabbage.
Roll it up and push in ends to form roll.
Put rolls into tomato soup and cook 1 1/2 hours.
If you don't like sauerkraut, leave it out and add 1 tablespoon vinegar instead.

title: creamy swiss onion soup
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons of butter; toss with bread cubes.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes; turn and bake 7 minutes longer or until toasted.
Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, saute onions in remaining butter until lightly browned, about 12 minutes.
Stir in water and bouillon; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup milk until smooth; gradually stir into onion mixture.
Stir in remaining milk.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes, stirring until thickened.
Reduce heat to low; stir in 3/4 cup Swiss cheese and pepper.
Ladle into four oven proof bowls.
Sprinkle with reserved croutons and remaining cheese.
Broil 4 inches from the heat until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Garnish with chives. Serves 4.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
Let Jell-O begin to gel, then add Tang, cheese and pineapple.
Return to refrigerator.
When starts to gel, fold in Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: special steak
directions: Put
round steak into crock-pot. Add special sauce. Add salt and pepper	to taste. Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours until tender. Great
for	working
women.
I
start in the morning, cook on low all day to evening.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and add 1/2 cup milk.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chowder
directions: Cook bacon and remove from skillet.
Use grease to cook onion and celery until tender.
Add potatoes and cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp or clams.
Mix flour and milk.
Add to mixture.
Cook until potatoes are done and serve with crackers.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix and spread in greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and serve with whipped cream, ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together with your hands, meat, onions, bell pepper, crackers, egg, salt and pepper.
Add about 1/2 can tomatoes and mix.
Make into 2 loaves and squeeze remainder of tomatoes on top of meat loaves.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cool.
Prepare crust as directed on package.
Spread into 12-inch pizza pan.
Spoon cooled sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes and Cheddar cheese.

title: frosted pumpkin-walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add brown sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin and flavorings. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and pumpkin pie spice. Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in walnuts. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Frost with Maple Frosting.
Yield:
7 1/2 dozen.

title: george's italian baked h. ola
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Mix all ingredients together and put in roaster and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 375°. (Check it out at 1 hour so it doesn't burn.)

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring beef broth to boiling.
Stir in barley, onion, garlic, basil, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until barley is nearly tender. Stir in mushrooms and carrot.
Simmer for 5 more minutes.

title: rum-raisin stuffed pears
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine pecans, raisins and sugar. Stir.
Add butter and mix well.
In a 1-quart casserole, arrange pear halves core side up.
Sprinkle pears with lemon juice.
Spoon half of pecan mixture over each pear; set aside.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stir and boil for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well.
Add apple and dressing just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, soups, broth and milk.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix stuffing, oil and broth.
Spread over the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Put vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake cup.
Beat rest of ingredients.
Pour over wafer in cupcake cup.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 18 cheesecakes.

title: steak sauce
directions: Marinate about 3 hours.

title: aunt gussies' sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Add flour until it makes a soft dough (3 3/4 to 4 cups).
Add baking soda and salt with flour.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: chicken 'n' dressing bake
directions: Boil chicken until cooked, then let cool in broth.
Bone and cut into bite sized pieces, reserving broth.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
Spread 2/3 of dressing mix on the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with chicken pieces.
Mix soups with 2 cups of the reserved chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining dressing.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat egg until frothy.
Add rest of ingredients until smooth. You cannot overbeat.
Best made a few hours before cooking and left to stand.
Put a few drops of oil in each section of a 12-capacity muffin pan.
Heat until oil bubbles.
Half fill each section with batter, dividing evenly into 12.
Put on top shelf of oven approximately 15 minutes until puddings are puffed and golden brown.
Serve immediately with any roast meat dinner.

title: peppie's apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, chop the apples and break the eggs over the apples and mix them well.
Add the sugars and mix together.
Add the vanilla, cinnamon and salt, mixing well and set aside.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Set oven at 400°.
In a nonstick 9-inch round cake pan (sprayed with nonstick oil) arrange rolls out flat.
Pour egg mixture over rolls.
Crumble sausages and sprinkle on eggs. Sprinkle the rest of the ingredients on top.
Bake until eggs are firm, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on crackers.

title: tomato and pastina soup
directions: In large pan, saute onion and garlic in oil for approximately 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth, Italian seasoning and fennel seed; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes with juice and pastina; bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: chop suey
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan to drain.
Brown pork in bacon fat.
Add vegetables, bacon, salt and pepper.
Combine sugar and cornstarch with water and pour over meat.
Cook for 1/2 hour, then add Worcestershire sauce.

title: tupperware pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a medium mixing bowl, seal and shake until coarse crumbs.
Remove seal.
Add egg (break the yolk), vinegar and ice water.
Shake again until it is a ball of dough.
(May be mixed in a bowl as regular pie crust.)
Makes 3 to 4 crusts.

title: caramel sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil.
Cook until sugar dissolves (about 1 minute).
Stir constantly.
Stir in ice cream.
Return to boil. Serve over ice cream or pound cake.
Great!

title: orange cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add butter, sugar, buttermilk, vanilla, flour, orange peel, dates, soda, and pecans.
Spoon into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick or straw.
When done, punch with ice pick.

title: golden party punch
directions: Dissolve the sugar in boiling water; let cool.
Combine the chilled juices.
Add sugar syrup.
Just before serving, stir in chilled ginger ale.
Put ice rings in punch bowl and serve.

title: apple pie filling cake
directions: Pour 1/4 cup oil in pan.
Add cake mix, eggs and water.
Stir with fork for 2 minutes. Swirl in pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box; bake in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with large fork.
Combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Carefully spread on cake.
Let soak down through cake.
Cool completely; fold 1/2 cup coconut in whipped topping.
Spread on cake.
Refrigerate.

title: sour cream sauce
directions: Beat egg yolks and sour cream together in top part of double boiler.
Place over simmering water and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is of custard consistency.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve at once with vegetables or fish.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute vegetables in large pot.
Squish up tomatoes and add with chicken broth.
Simmer 1 hour.
Brown smoked sausage and spareribs.
Add along with ham to vegetable mixture.
Add remaining ingredients except rice and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Add rice and simmer 25 more minutes.

title: dream whip surprise
directions: Crush graham crackers; add oleo, melted, and sugar.
Mix and pat (not too firmly) into 9 x 13 glass bake dish.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Fold in 1/2 package miniature marshmallows. Spread over cracker crust.
Top with your favorite pie filling. Chill several hours before serving or make a day ahead.

title: glazed fruit 'n' franks
directions: Drain pineapple and orange cans.
In medium saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook and stir until slightly thick.
Stir in franks and pineapple.
Heat and just before serving, stir in apple and oranges.
Serve warm with toothpicks.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Simmer eggplant in pan of boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Drain.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water 6 to 8 minutes or until tender; drain and set aside.
Gradually stir in milk into soup. Blend in egg, eggplant, onion and 3/4 cup stuffing.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Toss remaining one cup stuffing with butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken o'porto
directions: Cook mushrooms for 5 minutes in butter (remove with slotted spoon).
Take flour, pepper and nutmeg and combine.
Coat chicken, then brown chicken in leftover butter.
Stir in cream, wine and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling, then simmer for 15 minutes. Serve over rice pilaf.

title: magic quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of plate.
Place remaining ingredients in blender and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour mixture into pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray two 9-inch round cake pans.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs until mixture is very light and fluffy.
Add extract.
Combine flour and soda together, then add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Divide batter evenly in pans, spreading filling on top.
Sprinkle streusel topping over cherry filling.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: bean dip(lo-fat)
directions: Combine chilies, tomato sauce and onions and seasonings in a saucepan and cook until onions are tender.
Add beans and simmer until warmed through.
Serve either hot or cold.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Add bouillon cubes to boiling water.
Mix all ingredients except almonds.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir in almonds just before serving.

title: baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and dry apples.
Core each apple. Pare off upper fourth of apple skin.
Place apples in baking dish. Measure out sugar, butter and raisins.
Place in center of apple. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Fill dish with 1/2 cup water.
Bake, uncovered, until tender, approximately 45 minutes.
Spoon syrup from pan bottom over apples several times while baking.
Serve warm.
Pour 1/3 cup cream into each dish.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening with fork.
Add baking powder, salt and sugar; mix well.
Then add milk, knead about 2 tablespoons in hand then place in pan.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 14 (2 inch) biscuits.

title: candied kielbasa
directions: Place kielbasa in boiling water.
Cover kielbasa. Turn off heat, cover and let stand for 30 minutes. Drain.
Cool kielbasa. Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Combine sugar, mustard, cloves and juice. Pour over slices in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Heat ingredients and serve from crock-pot.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Mix in tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Mix in zucchini and cook for another 10 minutes.
Blend in noodles.
In a 12 x 7 inch baking dish layer 1/2 of meat and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat another layer.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: mountain pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, adding baking powder with the last of the flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Do not preheat oven.
Place in cold oven; turn oven on at 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven even once. Makes a large cake that keeps well and also is good frozen.

title: caramel rice krispies bars
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows; add Rice Krispies.
Spread 1/2 in a jelly roll pan (use 8 x 10-inch pan or larger).
Melt caramels, oleo and milk together.
Pour over Rice Krispies mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Melt chips on top.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Butter on both sides the 6 slices of bread.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put finely cut rhubarb on top of buttered bread. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Mix.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: You will need 2 pie crust.
You can buy the box with 2 crust or you can make your own.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until well blended. Sift flour, baking powder, spices and salt together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to egg mixture, beating after each addition.
When thoroughly mixed, form dough into a roll. Wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Slice crosswise and arrange on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Place on rack to cool.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar while still warm.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: kid's salad
directions: Toss fruits together.
Mix brown sugar and yogurt together. Then mix with fruit.
Serve chilled.

title: chili
directions: Dice onion in hamburger and brown.
Boil spaghetti; add drained hamburger, chili beans and tomato juice.
Add a pinch of sugar and chili powder.

title: coconut macaroon cake
directions: Mix with spoon (not mixer). Cream eggs with sugar.
Add milk and oil; mix well.
Add flour, then coconut and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake is done.
Then pour syrup mixture over hot cake.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap around a bunch of green beans; secure with a toothpick to fasten.
Make a glaze from margarine, brown sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour over bundles. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover the last few minutes.

title: tarragon vinaigrette
directions: Whisk all ingredients together in medium bowl.

title: gear's hot pepper hash
directions: Put onions and peppers through food grinder.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cover with 1
part vinegar and 2 parts water.
Let stand 20 minutes; drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Cook 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown the beef.
Add onions.
Cook until tender.
Mix with remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Bake in a 3-quart casserole dish, topped with bacon, at 350° for 1 hour, or in slow cooker for 5 to 6 hours.

title: choco bars
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and pour on greased cookie sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 17 minutes. Cover with the marshmallows and bake an additional 3 minutes. Cool.
Melt the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter and mix in the Rice Krispies. Spread on top of the marshmallows.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Boil water (once boiled), add bouillon cubes, carrots and onion (chopped small) add barley.
Cook until soft, add mushrooms. Make a roux, melt butter, add flour, stir in cold cream or milk and then stir until thick.
Once roux is finished combine vegetables and broth with the roux.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Brown in skillet the bread and margarine.
(I use one whole stick for a double batch of this recipe.)
Place on top of pineapple mixture and return to oven for 1/2 hour longer at same temperature.

title: double berry jam
directions: Measure 4 cups of fruit (fill last cup with water if necessary) into a large saucepan; add sugar.
Heat to a full rolling boil.
Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin; skim.
Pour into 8 hot scalded 1/2-pint jars.
Seal at once.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In skillet, brown sausage and drain well.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low setting 12 to 14 hours.
Serve topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings.
Form into small balls. Fry in cooking oil, turning frequently until light brown but not crusty on all sides.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread filling in bottom of a 8 by 12 inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts, and melted butter (mixture will be crumbly).
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: praline graham cookies
directions: Separate each graham cracker into 4 sections.
Arrange on a foil covered cookie sheet or spray sheet with Pam.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in sugar and nuts.
Bring to boil and cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Delicious!

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Top with French fried onions.
Put in glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until almost done; drain.
Add margarine to hot macaroni.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Drop from large spoon into skillet covered with hot fat.
Cook about 5 minutes. Drain on paper towels.

title: sourdough rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix together sourdough starter, salt, oil, flour and the yeast mixture.
Stir and mix well (no kneading).
Roll out and shape into rolls.
Put in greased pan; cover and let rise in warm place, about 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.

title: zucchini-parmesan bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together whole wheat and white flours, sugar, Parmesan, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix in zucchini.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs, milk and evaporated milk; blend.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: polenta con salsiccia
directions: Add mushrooms and sausage to skillet; cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms and sausage are lightly browned. Slowly stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pedernales river chili
directions: Sear meat in a large, dry skillet until lightly browned.
(You can use Pam if meat sticks too much.)
Add onion and garlic and saute.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, water and hot pepper sauce. Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour. Skim off any fat that accumulates.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt cheese and butter; mix with soup and broccoli.
Add rice. Put in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-ham tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Combine meat, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Stir in 3/4 cup soup mixture.
Divide meat mixture evenly between the tortillas and roll up.
Place seam side down in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir tomato into remaining soup and pour over top of tortillas with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable chac' o yuk
directions: Heat oil in frying pan or Chinese wok on high for about 2 minutes.
Brown meat quickly (if meat is already cooked, add after vegetables).
When no longer pink, add soy sauce, sugar, celery, pepper, cauliflowerets, bamboo shoots and onion.
Cook 1 minute. Add mushrooms, bean sprouts and 2 tablespoons of broth.
Cook 1 minute.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup broth; stir into vegetables. Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer, or until slightly thickened.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Core and dice apples.
In a large bowl, combine diced apples and lime or lemon juice.

title: herb potato rolls(makes 36)
directions: Prepare 1/2 cup mashed potatoes.
Pour warm water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water; add sugar and salt, stirring with wooden spoon until completely dissolved.
Let stand.
Add eggs, margarine, potatoes, 3 cups flour, oregano and sweet basil; mix until smooth.
Add rest of flour and mix until dough is smooth.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl; brush with melted margarine.
Cover and let raise in warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let raise again.
Knead dough lightly, shape and place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise until double (approximately 1 hour).
Brush with egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients with only half of the pecans.
Shape into any size balls that you wish.
Roll each ball into the remaining pecans.
These freeze well.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Fry ground beef; drain.
Blend in refried beans.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with uncooked lasagna noodles.
Spoon on 1/3 of the meat, 1/3 of the salsa and 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until it bubbles in the middle.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Pour over crackers and stir until well mixed. Pour into a large baking pan and bake in warm oven (250 degrees) for approximately 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven and spread out on paper towels until cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: rosemary chicken dinner(easy one-skillet dinner)
directions: Heat oil in electric skillet.
Brown garlic in oil.
Put chicken in pan; brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a fast boil, then cover and simmer for about 35 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix
together the peas, soup, pimento, cheese and eggs; put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and mix in margarine. Spread on top of casserole.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add 1 teaspoon sweetener, powdered milk, baking powder, then bread crumbs.
Beat slowly until bread crumbs are like dough.
Peel and slice apples into dough and mix in.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix cinnamon with sweetener and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Combine with onion and carrots. Boil until squash is just tender.
Drain.

title: cheesecake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and add 1 cup flour, put half of mixture into cake pan.
Mix the cheesecake filling, layer on cake mix in pan, add remaining cake mix and bake 1 hr-15 minutes.
Let cake cool, then ice and top with cherry pie filling.

title: al wright's clam chowder
directions: Steam clams to open.
Strain juice thoroughly.
Grind salt pork and brown in small pan.
Grind potatoes, carrots and onions. Put in a 5-quart pot.
Add water to cover; cook until almost tender.
Add pork, clams and juice.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add stewed tomatoes in the last 15 minutes.

title: double peppered chicken(hot and spicy)
directions: In a small bowl, stir first 9 ingredients until well combined. With hands, spread 1/2 cup of mixture evenly over chicken.
Place chicken into remaining seasoning mixture.
Close tightly. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Then grill, bake or broil.

title: oven barbecue spareribs
directions: Except for the spareribs, mix all ingredients together.
Cut the ribs into serving pieces.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.
Drain off fat.
Pour sauce over the ribs.
Bake for 1 hour longer at 350°.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat eggs into mixture.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and moist; do not overbake.
Cool on baking sheet for at least 2 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: In large skillet saute
onions and green pepper in oil. Add chicken and seasoning;
add
tomatoes
and
wine.
Cook 30 minutes over medium heat.
Add
soup
and
cook for 30 minutes more or until tender.
Cover while cooking.

title: green bean cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter, stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream and green beans.
Place in casserole and top with cheddar cheese.

title: chinese vegetable pizza
directions: Wash all veggies.
Cut squash, zucchini, and peppers into thin slices.
Quarter garlic.
Cut onion into thin stringy slices.
Mix all veggies well, add 5 Tbsp. soy sauce, garlic and black pepper, mix again.
Place veggies in lightly sprayed grilling basket.
Cook on BBQ grill for 15 minutes or until veggies get tender.
Heat oven to 375F.
Place bread on baking sheet, place veggies on top of bread in equal amounts.
Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese and dust with parmesan cheese.
Bake for 10-12 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Can be served with Jalapeno Soy Dip.

title: bro. rex's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes or longer.
(Delicious on cut up barbecue.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake on 350 for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini casserole
directions: Bake chicken.
Let cool and break into tiny bite size pieces. Set aside.
In mixing bowl combine the soup, mayo, milk and curry powder.
Add some garlic, pepper and onion powder.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed.
Pour into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Turn on wire rack to cool.

title: aunt bobbie's wild rice and sausage
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Brown vermicelli in butter.
Add rice, seasoning packet and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add browned sausage and drained mushrooms halfway through simmer time.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter in a bowl and melt in microwave 1 minute.
Remove from oven.
Stir well and cook another minute.

title: macaroni beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, garlic, onion and pepper and drain well.
Mix in all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with a small amount of grated cheese, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12 people.
This casserole freezes well.

title: pumpkin ice cream squares
directions: In large bowl, mix pumpkin, sugar, chopped nuts, salt, ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon until blended.
With spatula, fold in softened ice cream until well blended.
Arrange half of cookies in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

Spoon half of ice cream mixture over cookies. Top with remaining cookies, then remaining ice cream mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm, at least 5 hours. When ready to serve, add Cool Whip to each square.
I cover it completely with Cool Whip, then cut into squares.

title: cherry delight
directions: In small bowl, mix flour, butter and pecans.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Place meat and tomato juice in a large soup kettle.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Add salt and peppercorns; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Strain and cool overnight or until fat solidifies on top.
Remove fat and discard.
Remove meat from bones and return meat to broth; add the remaining ingredients except barley.
Simmer 1 hour.
At this time, barley can be added, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa; stir until dissolved.
Add hot water; stir.
With wire whip, blend in next 5 ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in pecans; pour into crust.
Bake on cookie sheet for 50 minutes, or until set.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: medallion sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Then add vanilla.
Add flour, alternating with milk.
Chill.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on a greased sheet at 400° for 9 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: carrot snack cakes
directions: *Stir flour, then spoon into measuring cup.

title: strawberry corn muffins
directions: Combine eggs, milk and vanilla in a small mixing bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
In a separate, larger bowl, combine flour, sugar, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Stir egg-milk mixture into dry ingredients along with melted butter until just mixed.
(Do not overmix.)
Batter will be lumpy.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour batter into a 12-cup buttered muffin tin.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, Karo syrup, water, oil, and cook over medium heat until syrup gets thready when you pick up spoon, then add peanuts.
Cook until roasted to your taste, then add the baking soda.
Quickly pour into a greased baking pan.

title: sweet pickle peaches
directions: Select firm, well
ripened
peaches and small enough to go in jars whole.
Make
syrup
of
vinegar and water, boil 10 minutes. Cook peeled
peaches
in boiling syrup until tender. Pack in sterilized jars.
Fill
jars
with boiling syrup and 3 or 4 whole cloves;
seal.

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: anise biscotti
directions: Into a large bowl, measure 1 1/2 cups of flour and remaining ingredients.
With a mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until just mixed.
Increase speed to medium and beat 3 minutes.
Scrape bowl occasionally with a rubber spatula.
With spoon, stir in remaining 1 cup of flour.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm (or place dough in freezer for 30 minutes).

title: tomato aspic
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on top of 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Place over low heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining tomato juice, salt, sugar, lemon juice, Worcestershire and hot pepper sauce. Stir until well blended.
Refrigerate until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in your own proportions of freshly cooked salad shrimp (or canned), hard-boiled egg, sliced green onion and frozen green peas.
Turn into serving bowl; chill and serve.

title: cheesecake mold
directions: Line a spring-form pan with ladyfingers on bottom and sides. Ladyfingers lining the sides of the pan should be snipped off on bottom end so that flat edge rests against the bottom cake layer. Mix cheese cake mix with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into lined pan.
Chill well.
Remove sides of pan and top with pie filling.

title: vegetable stir-fry
