directions: Combine oil, garlic, onion and mushrooms in a microwave casserole dish.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir in cauliflower, carrots and green pepper; cover with lid.
Microwave for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes; stir once.
Combine teriyaki sauce and cornstarch in 1-cup measuring glass.
Drain juices from vegetables into cup and mix well.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes; stir once.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Toss lightly.

title: pecan cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in hot water.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Prepare 6 cup ring mold with vegetable spray.
Chill until firm.

title: easy dirty rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a covered casserole dish for 40 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade hand and body cream
directions: These amounts will make 4 recipes of cream.
You will need 7 or 8 small butter tubs or any containers to put the cream in.

title: sweet pickle vegetables
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar and water.
Wash and cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Combine vegetables with vinegar mixture. Let stand at least 12 hours in refrigerator.
Will keep in liquid in refrigerator for a week.
Vegetables will stay crisp.
Very delicious.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add butter, vanilla and vinegar and stir together.
Pour water over this and stir, mixing well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour in batter.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: crabmeat divan
directions: Combine undiluted soup with shrimp or crabmeat.
Add sherry and mushrooms.
Place vegetable in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Top with seafood mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbling hot, about 25 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Form into balls and place singularly in casserole.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: mexican popcorn
directions: Mix butter, sauce and cheese together.
Drizzle over popcorn. Toss to mix.
Add salt to taste.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: In small frypan, cook bacon until brown and crispy (do not drain grease from bacon). Cook beans to package directions. Pour bacon over beans toss and serve.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add molasses and beaten egg.
Mix pumpkin pie spice into flour.
Add to other mixture alternating with milk.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chicken francaise
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until brown and set aside.
Return cooked cutlets to pan.
Add all of broth.
Squeeze in fresh lemon juice.
Add parsley flakes. Stir.
Simmer until sauce thickens.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Cut off crust and cut into cubes. Put layer of bread cubes into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs and add milk, paprika, mustard and salt. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325° until puffy and slightly brown.

title: no fuss chicken baked rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Arrange chicken on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
May be covered with foil if desired.

title: ginny's raspberry tomato salad
directions: Dissolve jello; chill until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: scallopini burgers
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, egg, milk, salt and dash of pepper. Shape into 6 patties.
Coat lightly with 1/4 cup flour.
Brown in hot cooking oil in skillet.
Drain fat.

title: christmas holly
directions: Melt margarine, marshmallows and food coloring together.
Stir in corn flakes until coated.
Drop on a buttered cookie sheet. Decorate with cinnamon red treats.

title: barbecued brown sugar salmon
directions: Take fresh salmon, filet, remove outside skin and white skin layer from meat.
Lay in deep (at least 2 inches deep) baking pan (that can be set on barbecue) with meaty sides up.
Melt butter in pan on stove; add chopped garlic.
Squeeze the juice from the lemons into the butter.
Add brown sugar and cook until bubbly. Pour butter mixture over salmon.
Salmon should be half submerged in butter mixture.
Set pan on barbecue rack over moderate heat. Barbecue needs to stay at moderate heat through cooking time. Baste salmon with the liquid around it so it will become glazed with the butter mixture.
Make sure the barbecue stays at an even temperature.
The butter should not boil or burn.
Cook until salmon will flake apart.
Time varies with temperature and size of salmon.
Half hour to an hour should work.

title: salmon st. james
directions: Lightly coat fillets with flour; fry in butter until done. Move cooked fish to dish.
Fry sliced onions; add garlic and sliced mushrooms.
Cook until done.
Add cream, clam stock, dill, parsley, brandy/sherry, salt and pepper; cook down.
Add Wondra flour to thicken.
Place the fried fillets back into thickened mixture to warm.
Serve with cooked pasta.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Mix equals parts of vinegar, water and sugar (enough to cover beef). Add onion, bay leaf, cloves and mace.
Cook until beef is done.
Thicken with gingersnaps soaked in water.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown onion and margarine in frying pan.
Pour into a bowl. Add bouillon soup, consomme soup and rice.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and nuts.
Add margarine and mix well. Stir in orange juice; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate.
Makes 4 dozen balls.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix instant pudding and pineapple together, then add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: jalapeno-cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in a double boiler until thickened.
Makes approximately 1 quart.
This will keep in refrigerator for about 2 weeks.

title: peachy dessert
directions: Melt margarine in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Mix all ingredients except peaches, and pour over margarine.
Arrange peaches on batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix together dressing, vinegar and oil; then mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 or 10-inch tube pan. Do not use electric mixer.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add these ingredients to the first mixture.
Mix in 3 cups fresh diced apples (peeled), 1 cup nuts and 1 cup raisins.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven at 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Also will make 2 loaf cakes.
(Use very large bowl for mixing.)
May be served topped with whipped cream.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix everything but pecans.
Pour everything into unbaked pie shell.
Put pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Insert knife halfway between center and edge.

title: candied violets
directions: In a bowl, beat egg whites with a wire whisk just until frothy. Place sugar in another bowl.
Taking one violet at a time, pick it up by the stem and dip into egg whites, covering all surfaces. Gently dip into the sugar, again being sure all surfaces are covered.
Place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Snip stems off. Using a toothpick, open petals to original shape.
Sprinkle sugar on any uncoated area.
Dry in a 200° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until sugar is crystallized.
Gently remove violets to wire rack with a spatula or two tined fork.
Sprinkle again with sugar if violet appears syrupy.
Cool; store in airtight container with wax paper between layers.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Note:
If you have about 6 to 8 hours on and off during the day, It's easy and kids love it (adults too).

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine the seasoning mix ingredients (first 8) in a small bowl and set aside.
Place the vegetable oil, gizzards, pork and bay leaves in a large skillet over high heat; cook until meat is thoroughly browned, about 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the seasoning mix, then add the onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic; stir thoroughly, scraping pan bottom well.
Add the butter and stir until melted.
Reduce heat to medium and cook about 8 minutes, stirring constantly and scraping pan bottom well (if you're not using a heavy-bottomed skillet, the mixture tends to stick to the bottom of the pan).
Stir in chicken stock and stir until the mixture sticking to the pan bottom comes loose; cook about 8 minutes over high heat, stirring once.
Then stir in the chicken livers and cook about 2 minutes.
Add the rice and stir thoroughly; cover pan and turn heat to very low; cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and leave covered until rice is tender, about 10 minutes.
(The rice is finished this way so as not to overcook the livers and to preserve their delicate flavor.)
Remove bay leaves and serve immediately.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, pepper, ketchup, sugar, mustard and vinegar to beef and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: gone-all-afternoon beef stew
directions: Place all into lightly greased 3-quart casserole with tight-fitting lid.
Bake at 225° for 5 hours.

title: texas delight cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in long 13 x 19-inch pan.
Let cool.
Punch holes in cake with knife or fork.
Mix pineapple with juice and 1 cup sugar.
Let it come to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cake; let cool.
Mix instant pudding mix as directed on box.
Spread on cake.
Slice bananas and put on cake.
Spread 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut or both.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake 15 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Use chopped nuts on top when using this for your pineapple cake.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and all spices.
Blend well. Hollow out middle of bread, leaving a bit in the bottom.
Pour dip mixture into bread.
Bread removed from center may be torn up and used with the dip.

title: tomato and zucchini crepes
directions: In a skillet, bring tomatoes, onion and seasonings to a boil. Add zucchini and continue to cook on medium heat until crisp-tender.
Combine cornstarch with 2 tablespoons tomato mixture and add to skillet.
Stir and cook until well thickened.

title: super simple coconut pie
directions: Beat milk and pudding 1 minute.
Add Cool Whip; stir gently. Sprinkle coconut on bottom of crushed crackers.
Pour pudding mix on top of coconut.
Sprinkle more coconut on top of pie.
Chill, then serve.

title: cheese - kiwi sandwich
directions: Cover bread slices with cheese; broil until cheese bubbles. Remove from oven; top with kiwi slices in decorative manner in center of each sandwich.
Combine mayonnaise and shrimp; spoon on top of kiwi slices.
Serve at once.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to 3 or 4 weeks.
Stir before serving.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix together the jelly, French dressing and onion soup mix. Pour over chicken in a baking pan, making sure chicken is coated with mixture.
Bake for 1 hour (or until chicken is done) in a 375° oven.
Delicious and easy!

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomato sauce and form into a loaf.
Place in roaster pan.
Pour the tomato sauce over loaf and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: steak and ale marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Marinate steaks or chicken overnight and grill.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix.
Serve with fajitas, eggs or whatever.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients and chill. Take round bread and hollow out.
Put dip in center of bread. Serve.

title: oriental chicken buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, ginger, garlic and soy sauce in a medium skillet.
Cook to boiling.
Add chicken.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes until chicken becomes opaque.
Remove from heat. Remove chicken from ginger liquid.
Combine cornstarch and water. Stir into the ginger liquid.
Return to heat and heat to boiling, stirring continuously.
Cook until clear and thickened.
Stir in chicken, chestnuts and onion.
Remove from heat.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Spread Cream Cheese on bottom of 8x12 dish.
Brown and drain the sauce and crumble over cream cheese.
Sprinkle peppers and onions over sausage.
Cover with pecante sauce.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese over and -20 minutes at 350 until hot and bubbly and cheese melts.
Serve with Tortilla Chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and mayonnaise; mix rest up.
This can be made in a ball or in the shape of a wreath at Christmas.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook
meat
with onions until tender.
Drain fat.
Pour some meat
and onion mixture over tortillas in a large casserole
dish. Mix
cheese,
soups, sauce and milk together in a saucepan.
Heat until
cheese
is
melted.
Pour some of this over
meat
and tortillas.
Put
another
layer
of quartered tortillas on top with meat mixture and repeat until tortillas, meat and
sauce
are used.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Saute celery, onions and garlic.
Add clam juice, water, potatoes, carrots and bay leaf. Cook 15 minutes.
Add haddock, scallops, lobster, water, clams and half and half or cream.
Simmer.
Add salt, pepper and bacon.

title: oriental cabbage
directions: Cut green pepper into strips.
Chop celery and carrots thin and slanted.
Slice onions into rings.
Melt butter and add vegetables in large skillet.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are as tender as you like.
Stir in milk and heat thoroughly.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

title: hopscotch
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Then add marshmallows and potato sticks.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and refrigerate.

title: perfect meringue
directions: In small saucepan, combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in cornstarch mixture.
Spread on filling. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hurry up vegetable soup
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with electric mixer. Add melted butter, sugar, flour and milk. Beat again until well blended. Stir in coconut. Pour into 2 ungreased 8-inch pie pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut. Makes 16 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples and water in a buttered casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and margarine until the consistency of corn meal. Add pecans. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly lemon pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks with sugar, lemon peel and juice until light.
Cook, stirring in top of double boiler over boiling water until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool thoroughly.
Fold in half the whipped cream.
Turn into Meringue Crust and refrigerate at least 2 hours to set.
Fold powdered sugar into remaining whipped cream and spread over chilled pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: one dish meal
directions: In a casserole dish put ingredients in order given.
Cover and bake at 400° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes for chops to brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook filling, then alternate vanilla wafers with bananas in Pyrex dish (deep).
Cover with filling when filling is thickened. May be topped with meringue.

title: sweet sour jerky
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together in a bowl.
Dip meat slices into marinade.
Place dipped meat layers in bowl.
Pour remaining sauce over meat.
Cover tightly.
Let marinate in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours.
Take out and place in dehydrator until dry.
Blot excess oil with paper towel.

title: quick tamale pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add salsa, cheese soup, olives and salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Prepare Jiffy mix following directions on box.
Spoon on mixture.
Bake until cornbread is brown at 350°.
Add Mozzarella cheese for topping. Melt.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Boil 1 cup of water and pour into a bowl; dissolve the jello and add strawberries, constantly stirring until thawed.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill until set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup nuts.
Shape into ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Refrigerate.
Let it set to room temperature awhile before serving.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Break corn cobs into pieces. Put in large pot. Cover with water and bring to a rolling boil. Boil for 30 minutes. Add water during boiling period to maintain about same water level. Remove cobs and strain liquid. Measure 3 cups of liquid into a

larger saucepan; stir in pectin. Bring to a full, rolling boil; then add sugar. Bring again to boiling, stirring until sugar is melted. Boil hard for 1 minute. Just before removing from heat, you add oil of cinnamon for flavor.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into one prepared pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: puerto rican omelette
directions: Low heat, no fat and a good 6 to 8-inch Teflon skillet are the secrets to this great meal!

title: honey garlic pork chops
directions: Combine marinade ingredients; pour over pork chops.
Place in an airtight container; refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.
Remove pork chops from marinade; reserve marinade.
Grill pork chops 5 inches from heat source for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.
Baste occasionally with reserved marinade.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and set aside.
Cream eggs, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oatmeal.
Spoon dough in 1-inch balls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: chicken casserole with crescent rolls
directions: Cook the chicken and cut up fine.
Pour chicken soup in a large casserole dish.
Put chicken in each crescent roll and roll up.
Put rolls in soup and bake at 375° until rolls are brown. Put cheese over each roll and put in oven until cheese is melted. Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until just tender; drain.
Reserve 1 cup liquid.
Melt butter.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Blend in flour.
Add broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in 1 cup liquid reserved from broccoli, heavy cream, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and pepper.
Add broccoli; heat to boiling.
Stir in cheese. Serve sprinkled with chives.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in water until done.
Drain.
Mix with soup, corned beef, milk, onion and cheese.
Pour in lightly greased dish. Crush potato chips and spread on top.
Bake in a 425° oven until bubbly and chips are brown.

title: plum tomato and pesto bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place bread, cut side up, on cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Spread each bread half with pesto sauce; top with tomato slices.
Sprinkle with olives and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut into slices to serve.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: italian string beans(low-fat, no sugar)
directions: Cook beans until partially tender; drain and saute them in olive oil, 1 clove mashed garlic and oregano.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender but not too soft.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In baking dish, arrange broccoli and chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
In cup, combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: wollybear dessert
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer ingredients as they are listed, except oleo.
Drizzle oleo over all the ingredients.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dredge chicken parts in flour and place skin side down in baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°. Remove chicken from pan and add the next 7 ingredients.
Stir well.
Add chicken broth and stir.
Place the chicken on top of the rice mixture, skin side up, and bake for 40 to 45 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german pound cake
directions: All ingredients must be at room temperature.
In large bowl cream butter.
Sift the two sugars together and add gradually to butter.
Add unbeaten egg yolks, one at a time, and beat until smooth.
Mix in extracts.
Sift flour together with baking powder and salt 3 times.
Starting and ending with flour, add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Grease Bundt pan.
Place 24 whole almonds in bottom of pan, securing with a dab of butter.
Place another ring of remaining almonds on side of pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack or serving plate to complete cooling.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Add carrots and nuts. Bake in two layer pans at 325° for 45 minutes; cool.

title: muffin-biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in muffin tins at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut flour and shortening together.
In a cup, measure 6 level tablespoons of flour, salt and warm water.
Blend with fork.
Pour over flour and shortening mixture and cut in.
Roll out dough as you would with any pie dough.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Mix sugar, sour cream, margarine and eggs in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 1 minute.
Beat in bananas and vanilla on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat in remaining dry ingredients on medium speed, scraping bowl, for 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Brown Butter Frosting.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2 inch bars.
Yields 48 bars.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart dish. Scald milk with 1/4 cup butter. Blend all ingredients. Place baking dish in pan of hot water 1-inch deep. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Pudding will be done when knife is inserted 1-inch from edge of pan and comes out clean. Serve warm with cream over top.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and set aside while mixing cake.
Cream well the sugar, margarine and Mazola oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour mixed with cinnamon and soda.
Mix well.
Then mix in oat mixture.
Pour cake mixture into oblong pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add the egg and milk; stir gradually to make a smooth batter.
Add melted butter.
Makes 9 medium pancakes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine with hands the hamburger, onion, bell pepper, eggs, crackers, salt and pepper.
Combine a little of the tomato sauce in with it all.
After it is all mixed together, shape it into a round ball and put it into your baking pan.
Flatten a little.
Pour your remaining tomato sauce over it. Bake for 2 hours.
Serves about 5 to 6.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in oil.
Add next 4 ingredients. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
In large baking dish, cover bottom with torn tortilla shells.
Pour 1/3 chicken mixture on tortillas, spreading evenly.
Layer with 1/3 olives and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat layers 2 more times, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. (Ole, Ole, Ole!)

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in warm water.
Melt margarine; cream with sugar in a large bowl, add egg.
Add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture. Then add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in tightly covered bowl and keep in refrigerator.
To cook, drop by spoon into well-greased 2-1/2 inch muffin tins and bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes, or until browned.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: diabetic-sweet potato surprise
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until soft.
Remove skins.
Mash potatoes well, adding orange juice until they have the consistency of applesauce.
Chill.
Just before serving this dessert, fold in fruit and nuts.

title: pan coat
directions: Combine
ingredients and use first speed of mixer for 1 minute to smooth.
Cream on second speed.
Whip light on third speed. Use for greasing pans.
Need not be refrigerated.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Beat eggs and water.
Bring broth to a boil.
Reduce heat and stir in sugar, salt and soy sauce, keeping heat very low.
Slowly add egg and water mixture, stirring constantly, until separated into shreds.
Turn off heat and serve immediately.
Garnish with scallions.

title: chicken-like salad
directions: Add thyme to mayonnaise and mix well.
Combine all ingredients and toss until well mixed.
Allow to refrigerate for several hours before serving on crisp lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Make 4 layers out of cake mix.
Drain pineapple and oranges on paper towel.
Chop oranges (save some slices for top of cake).
Mix all ingredients, set in refrigerator.
Frost between layers, top and sides.

title: cherry swirled cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven 300°. Spray a 8 in. spring form pan. Sprinkle crumbs on bottom of pan. Puree cherry pie filling, add orange rind, and set aside. Beat cheese until fluffy, gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth. Add egg whites, egg, lemon juice and the vanilla. Mix well, stir in flour. Pour half of the batter in prepared pan. Spoon 1/2 cup of cherry puree evenly over batter. Top with remaining batter. Drop by spoonful, 1/2 cup of cherry puree over the batter. With a knife gently swirl. Bake 60 to 65 minutes. Let cool and chill. Serve with remaining puree if desired.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and cook for 20 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Let cook, then refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts. Will keep in refrigerator for a few weeks.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Pour milk in.
Beat the egg yolks and mix with the other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat on stove eye until thick.
Line big bowl with wafers, then pudding and bananas. Repeat until all has been added.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the ingredients listed in the left column. Chill dough.
Form dough into 1-inch rolls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes; bake 2 1/2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not let the cookies brown.
Remove from oven and while the cookies are still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely.
Roll in powdered sugar again.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind or chop peppers and onions.
Place in saucepan; cover with hot water and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Makes 2 pints.

title: patty's pineapple desserts
directions: Note:
Use 1 full 12 ounce Cool Whip and half of other 12 ounce Cool Whip when mixing ingredients, saving other half for top of dessert.

title: chicken in white wine and yogurt sauce
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Place chicken in pan. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt remaining butter in saucepan; add flour and cook briefly, stirring.
Add broth, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and smooth.
Add yogurt, wine and lemon and pepper, stirring until blended.
Remove pan from oven.
Turn each chicken breast.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked.

title: mexican delight
directions: Saute onion in cooking oil, then brown meat.
Add sauce, corn, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: peek-a-boo cake
directions: Spread dough in bottom of 9 x
13-inch
pan.
Drop
pie filling by tablespoons on top (one
tablespoon
to
each serving). Bake at 350° for 30 to
minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top while hot.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Bake pie crust until lightly browned.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Fill pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the top browns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix
melted
margarine	and
crushed crackers together. Put half of cracker mixture into bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Mold into a ball and chill.
Roll ball in rest of nuts.

title: gourmet sauerkraut
directions: Mix all together and cook for about 30 minutes.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour and	salt.
Add milk, egg, 1 cup cheese, bread crumbs and crab meat.
Mix together, pour in greased casserole and top with 1/2 cup cheese and corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, water and pudding; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in a large bowl (pudding, cookies and bananas).

title: hunter's stew
directions: Flour pieces of meat, then brown in shortening.
Remove and set aside.
Brown onion separately after meat.
Add tomato soup and 1 soup can water.
Add bouillon cube, basil, thyme, ketchup, cut up carrots, cut up potatoes, garlic clove or powder, pepper and Gravy Master for color.
Cook 2 hours or until meat is tender and vegetables are soft.

title: bar squares
directions: Mix cereal and 1 cup marshmallows in a large mixing bowl. Place remaining ingredients in a saucepan over low heat until completely melted.
Pour over cereal mixture and press into a slightly greased pan.

title: brown gravy with pork chops on side
directions: Gravy: Add cornstarch to the water with pork drippings for thickness. Add salt and pepper for taste.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix in all ingredients.
Fix day before served.
Very good with Escort crackers or Waverly Wafers.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix together rice, ground turkey, salt, and pepper.
Make balls a little larger than a walnut size.
In a pressure cooker put in tomato soup and water.
Mix well.
It is best to place the balls on a rack.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let cool 5 minutes before opening pressure cooker.

title: chicken salad spread
directions: Blend all ingredients in a food processor or blender; refrigerate.

title: roquefort spread
directions: Soften Roquefort cheese and cream cheese; blend with mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, onion and lemon juice.
A perfect dip for cauliflowerets.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In small skillet, melt margarine.
Saute green pepper and onion until crisp-tender.
Combine both cans of corn, eggs and corn muffin mix in a large bowl.
Mix well. Add skillet mixture.
Blend well. Pour into casserole. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until firm and set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Delicious!
Great side dish for turkey or ham.

title: custard pie
directions: Brush pie shell with egg white; let dry.
Preheat oven to 425°. Use lower shelf in oven.
Mix small amount of water with dry ingredients.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add the rest of flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400 for 25 minutes; turn over to 325° until knife inserted on outside edge of custard comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Let set and center will finish cooking.
Sprinkle nutmeg on filling just before you bake.

title: hot dog chili(for a group)
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain off grease.
Mix in catsup, soup, worcestershire sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to make a good consistency.
Cook slowly until done, stirring often.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix and heat.
Pour over chicken wings.
Let marinate 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork roast
directions: Before pouring gravy over roast, remove fat in bottom of pan. Remove roast from pan and let cool before slicing.
Serve with rice.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Beat eggs and add pecans.
Add hot syrup gradually.
Pour hot filling into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375° or until center is firm.

title: winter slaw
directions: Mix and refrigerate 24 hours before eating.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add eggs.
Melt margarine and add milk and vanilla.
Beat well and add nuts.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and reserve.
Brush caps with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Place, hollow side up, in shallow pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter and oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not brown!
Finely mince mushroom stems and squeeze them in a towel to extract juice; discard juice.
Add stems and shallots to onions.
Cook over moderately high heat; stir frequently.
After 6 to 8 minutes, mushroom pieces should begin to separate and brown lightly.
Add wine and boil it down rapidly until almost evaporated.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 pan.
Melt butter and peanut butter chips for 2 minutes in microwave on high.
Stir in milk and marshmallows and microwave 1 minute on high.
Put half peanuts on bottom of pan. Pour mixture over peanuts and add rest of peanuts on top.
Press down.
Refrigerate until set.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, margarine and vanilla; mix well by hand.
Add slightly beaten eggs and mix in (do not cook).
Add pecan pieces.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
(Optional: Garnish with whole pecans on top.) Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chips.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinate pork tenderloins several hours or overnight.
Ziploc bag can be used.
Charcoal tenderloins on grill for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grilled roast beef
directions: Start grill fire two hours in advance; less on electric grill. Set grill 5-inches from heat.
Grill 30 minutes on each side.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add eggs, softened margarine and powdered sugar into bowl.
Beat for 10 minutes, until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas; add to top of mixture.
Top with pineapple, Cool Whip, pecans and diced cherries.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In a warm bowl, add the warm water, yeast, salt, sugar, oil and slightly beaten egg.
Add enough flour to make dough consistency in texture (firm enough to handle, but not too firm). Let rise, then knead down and roll out like a biscuit into muffin tins.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt, soda and add milk, corn, cheese and eggs. Mix well, add onions, pepper and bacon drippings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in iron skillet.

title: hot spinach dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave cream cheese in casserole on High 30 seconds.
Add seasonings and milk and stir well.

title: tommie's cheese sandwich souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Trim crust off bread.
Layer 3 slices of bread.
Cut into 3 finger sandwiches.
Frost each one on all sides except bottom.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place frozen finger sandwiches in ziplock bags and freeze.
When ready to serve, take out the number needed and place on cookie sheet prepared with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry cake
directions: *Can use sweet cherries and omit sugar.

title: creamy chocolate(serves 2)
directions: Blend all ingredients on medium until creamy.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
If apples are sweet, use 1/3 less sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cod with caper sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place fillets in pan; cover and bake for 10 minutes or until fish is flakey.

title: decorator's frosting (1 cup)
directions: Cream butter;
gradually
beat in sugar and salt.
Stir in milk, egg yolk and vanilla; stir until smooth.
If desired, tint with vegetable
dye,
one
drop
at a time, so that color remains appealingly delicate.

title: 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until well blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool; refrigerate ovenight.

title: no sugar dessert
directions: Mix together and cover with Dream Whip.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and place in casserole dish. Melt butter.
Place crackers on top of vegetables and pour butter over crackers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: triple vegetable scallop
directions: Cook potatoes
and onions in boiling salt water until tender; drain and return to kettle. Melt butter in large saucepan; stir in flour and bouillon cubes.
Stir and crush cubes.
Add milk and stir until sauce thickens.
Drain mushrooms and add to sauce. Fold sauce into potatoes and onions.
Spoon into greased 12 cup baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are toasted.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
In same pan, add to ground beef the soup, bouillon cubes and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve over noodles.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Mash.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: almond bark bars
directions: Melt almond bark and stir in the chunky peanut butter.
Add dry roasted peanuts, miniature marshmallows and Rice Krispies.
May be dropped on wax paper or put in a greased pan.

title: hot christmas drink
directions: Combine and simmer in crock and serve in mugs.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together
raisin
bran,
flour,
sugar,
salt
and soda; set aside.
Add buttermilk,
eggs and oil.
Mix all together and beat until well moistened.
Bake any
amount
you
desire
for
12 to 15 minutes in a greased muffin tin.
Batter may be kept in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Delicious served HOT with butter and honey!

title: macaroon pie
directions: Fold in egg whites to egg yolk mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake 35 or more minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease cookie sheet or shallow pan well and line with waxed paper.
Beat 3 eggs until foamy, add 1 cup sugar and beat.
Add pumpkin and mix.
Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture and beat.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on powdered sugar towel.
Pull off wax paper and roll up from the long side.
Cool well.

title: nine day salad
directions: Sprinkle 1 c. sugar over above and set aside

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Mix cheese, bread and flour. Add cooked and drained sausage. Put in large casserole dish. Beat eggs. Add milk, salt and pepper to taste. Pour over ingredients in casserole. Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set in middle. Cool 10 minutes before serving. Serves 10 to 12.

title: ooey googy caramel bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oats, baking soda and melted butter. (If you substitute margarine for butter, use 2 tablespoons less.) Press 2/3 mixture onto bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water, pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Mix together and refrigerate.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 38 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
The casserole dish should be covered.

title: mary's artichoke dip
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden on top.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Sift the flour, soda and salt together 3 times.
Add the corn oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Prepare apples and nuts.
Add flour, a little at a time, to sugar mixture.
Add apples and nuts last.
Mix well.
Put in oven set at 325° and bake 45 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: You will need a tube pan, buttered and floured lightly.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and brown on top. Makes a large casserole or two small ones.

title: quick veggies
directions: Place frozen vegetables in baking dish.
Cover with Italian dressing.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Note:
You will need an 8-inch clay pot, a trowel, fake flowers and gummy worms (optional).

title: hash browns and cheese casserole
directions: Slightly thaw potatoes and combine 1/2 cup melted butter, salt and pepper.
Add onion, soup, sour cream and cheese, blending thoroughly.
Pour into buttered casserole (3 quart).
Mix corn flake crumbs with 1/4 melted butter and sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix vegetables, soup and milk together in big bowl. Fold in chicken. Fill 1 pie crust with mixture. Top with second crust. Pinch edges to seal. Brush top with slightly beaten egg. Bake for 1 hour.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: In a frying pan, cook green pepper and onion in butter

until tender. Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and eggplant. Cook slowly for 10 minutes. Pour mixture into a greased casserole. Spread bread crumbs evenly on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until eggplant is tender. Serves 6.

title: chicken enchilada casserole(serves 6)
directions: Cut tortillas into quarters and layer on bottom of greased casserole bowl.
Arrange a layer of chicken, olives, chiles, onions and cheese.
Repeat a layer.
Mix soups and pour over top. Allow to soak through.
Top with more cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat in margarine in a large skillet. Add onion, celery, green pepper, garlic and seasonings.
Mix well.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Add rice and parsley.
Mix lightly. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix margarine, beaten eggs, sugar and corn syrup together.
Add a little salt or you can leave it out.
Put in 1 cup pecans and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch homemade pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: eva's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Use same water.
Add ingredients with the pork on top.
Bake at 375°.
Place in oven in early morning for an early supper.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot.

title: instant salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cocoa.
Add milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients in 3 additions, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean. Invert onto a wire rack; cool.

title: fresh tomato pie
directions: Cover bottom of greased shallow baking dish with 1 cup fresh bread crumbs.
Add alternating layers of tomatoes, onions and cheese.
In a bowl, combine eggs, salt, pepper and oregano.
Blend well and pour over layered tomatoes, cheese and onions.
Sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup bread crumbs.

title: lipton onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Chill.
Serve with chips or as vegetable dip.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip by mixing milk, vanilla and topping mix in deep narrow bottom bowl.
Beat on high speed with electric mixer about 4 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peak.
Set in refrigerator.
Separate eggs.
Put egg yolks in medium bowl and stir.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice, a little at a time.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour mixture into crust prepared from Nilla wafers.
Whip egg whites, adding about 5 to 6 tablespoons sugar.
Pour on top of pie, spreading to edges.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until light brown.
Place Nilla wafers around edge prior to baking.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, sugar and seasonings in 1 1/2 quart casserole, cover, microwave 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes on high.
Stir in Smokies.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Butter bread slices on both sides, then cube bread slices and layer in bottom of baking dish. Brown sausage (drain).
Crumble sausage over bread cubes.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and cheese and pour over sausage and bread cubes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Gradually add 1/2 cup of sugar and salt, beating constantly.
Add milk and cream gradually.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick enough to coat spoon. Cool.
Add sherry extract and chill.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add the rest of sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold into chilled custard.
When ready to serve, pour into chilled punch bowl.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: raisin creme pie
directions: Put raisins in hot water to soften about 15 to 20 minutes. Mix all together. Drain raisins and put into mixture and walnuts. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: In medium mixing bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients. Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine egg, oil and milk.
Stir in chopped apple.
Add egg mixture all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until just moistened. Stir in nuts and raisins, if using.

title: colorful pineapple pork
directions: In a skillet, combine 1 cup water, sugar, vinegar and salt. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; add the pork, cucumber, carrot, pineapple, tomato, green pepper and soy sauce. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until heated through. Combine the cornstarch and remaining water until smooth. Stir into skillet. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Serve over rice. Yield: 2 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil and
prepare macaroni.
Cut boiled eggs.
Dice Spam and brown.
Dice onion and brown.
Heat peas and drain.
Put it in a big bowl
and mix with mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(microwave)
directions: Mix brown sugar and melted butter in 8-inch round glass cake dish.
Use cook cycle and cook until a syrup is formed (3 to 4 minutes); add pineapple and cherries.
Add the batter mix according to directions on box, using pineapple juice and water to give the amount of liquid called for on the box.
Cover with paper towel and bake 7 minutes.
Remove immediately from dish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a skillet use 3 tablespoons oil.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add tomatoes; cook until well blended.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and stir often until thickened.
Cook meat until well done in a separate skillet. Drain off fat.
Add to sauce and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheesy zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Place dried mushrooms in small bowl. Cover with the boiling water. Let soak for 30 minutes or until the mushrooms have softened. Strain mushrooms, reserving liquid. Chop the mushrooms

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup water.
Add boiling water, lemon juice, juice from pineapple and sugar.
Let sit in freezer until syrupy (10 to 15 minutes). Break cake and put 1/2 into a large pan. Whip 3 envelopes of topping.
Fold in gelatine mixture and pineapple.
Pour over cake. Add remaining 1/2 of cake and top with rest of gelatine mixture. Add the remaining envelope of topping on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serves many.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over the bread and let set until all is moist.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 370° for 1 hour.

title: pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Add 4 cups flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix well.
On a lightly floured surface, knead the mixture well with your hands.
Roll pieces of dough into any shape you like.
Place them on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
In a small bowl, beat Egg Beaters. Brush the tops of the dough with the Egg Beaters.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake the pretzels at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
18 big soft pretzels.

title: can't fail caramels
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup, cream, milk and butter.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly to 248° (or when small quantity into cold water forms firm balls).
Remove from heat; add vanilla extract.
Pour onto greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
When firm, turn out on board and cut into squares.
Wrap squares in wax paper.

title: butter whole egg cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Stir ingredients together and put in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
May add one can drained oysters.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Combine ingredients.

title: come easy - go easy cookies
directions: Break crackers at indented places and put on a 10 x 14-inch cookie sheet. Have crackers touching. Place a pecan half on each cracker. Mix margarine, butter and sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Turn to medium heat and boil exactly 3 minutes. (Use a 3 minute egg timer.) Pour hot mixture over crackers. Bake in a 350° oven 9 or 10 minutes.
Will be bubbly. Immediately remove to cooling rack with spatula.

title: peanut butter pie #5
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk together until smooth and creamy. Add Cool Whip and blend. Pour this mixture into the pie crust and chill.

title: syllabuh
directions: Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold in sugar and rum or brandy. Cover and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour or so.
Serve in sherbet glasses or punch cups with a faint dusting of nutmeg. Serves 4.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Reserve for topping.
In an 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan, empty the cherry pie filling.
Spread on bottom.
Spread topping over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick beer rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 12-15 minutes or until it turns light brown at 350°. Remove from oven and sprinkle miniature marshmallows on.
Return to oven for about one minute.
Remove from oven and flatten slightly with spatula.
While the above is in oven; heat corn syrup, margarine and peanut butter chips until melted over low heat.
Add salted peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Spread over cake and marshmallow mixture.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: smoky clam cheese roll
directions: Drain clams; shape 1 package cream cheese long and flat, 15 x 2-inches.
Place over clams; tuck in ends.
Roll and press to seal seams, using waxed paper to assist rolling.
Roll in parsley and nuts.
Chill.
Cut and spread on bread.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook
milk and cornmeal together in heavy bottomed pan. (Mixture will
be
very thick.) Add corn, tomatoes, olives and chili powder.
Brown pork
and
onions,
then
add to mixture. Bake in large greased casserole
dish
for
1 hour at 350° (or put in smaller casserole
dishes
and
freeze
for later use). Serves six to ten.

title: hashbanana berry shake
directions: Place ice milk, banana and strawberries into food processor. Process until smooth.
Thin to desired consistency with milk. Pour into glass and drink.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Mix all the above together. Put into ball and serve with crackers.

title: 22 minute cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Combine flour and sugar in large bowl.
Set aside.
Bring to boil the butter, water, Crisco and cocoa. Gradually mix with flour and sugar mixture.
Combine buttermilk, eggs and soda; mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and margarine in small bowl. Press into spring-form pan (9-inch). Sprinkle gelatin over water in small saucepan. Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved. Add 1/4 cup gel mix to pie filling. Stir in 2 teaspoons almond liqueur. Pour cherry mix over crust. Refrigerate until set (30 minutes).

title: cinnamon pickles (rings)(makes 4 quarts, big mouth jars)
directions: Peel and ream out seeds from cucumber rings (if making rings). Can slice or make sticks using medium cucumbers.
In large crock, mix lime into 8 1/2 quarts cold water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash cucumbers.
Return to clean container and soak in cold water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Place in large enamel pan and cover with cold water.
Mix well vinegar, alum and food coloring.
Add to cucumbers and simmer for 2 hours.
Drain.
Make syrup (make 1/2 more to have enough) with vinegar, sugar and 2 cups cold water. Bring to a boil.
Then add red hots and cinnamon sticks.
Melt all candy.
Pour over cucumbers.
Next morning, pour syrup off and bring to a boil.
Pour back over cucumbers.
Second morning, repeat.
Third morning, pour syrup off and bring to a boil.
Place cucumbers in jars and cover with the syrup.
Seal, leaving the cinnamon sticks out.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine in saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Place cut up skinned chicken pieces in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more, basting occasionally.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add seasonings.
Add corn and soup and blend.
Make mashed potatoes according to directions (or use fresh).
Put potatoes on top of hamburger mixture in 4 mounds. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and press in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 6 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let cool.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato soup (undiluted) and the green beans (juice and all).
Add seasoned salt.
Bring mixture to a boil in the skillet and then turn down to simmer.
Combine cornbread mix and egg and enough milk to make a soft mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto the simmering meat mixture until evenly distributed on top.
Place cover on skillet and simmer for about 10 minutes or until the cornbread has risen and has become firm.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Serves 6.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk. Add other ingredients and pour over wafers and stir.

title: potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Add the rest of the ingredients, then bake at 250° for about 20 to 30 minutes until hot.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large saucepan, beat together the eggs and milk.
Add the sugar and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for about 10 minutes or until the mixture is thickened.
Don't let it boil or the eggs will curdle.
The mixture is thick enough when it coats the back of a spoon smoothly.
Cool and then stir in the cream and vanilla.
It's best to cover the mixture and refrigerate overnight before churning it in an ice cream maker.
This ice cream has 250° calories per half cup serving.

title: cream rounds
directions: Mix ingredients. Spread thin on baguette slices. Sprinkle with paprika. Broil until bubbly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
Remove pie crust from freezer.
Use a wire whisk to mix together filling ingredients in order given.
Re-crimp edge of pie crust to stand 1/2-inch above rim.
Place pie crust on heated baking sheet.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake in the center of oven 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Saute onion, pepper, garlic, celery and parsley in oleo.
Add salt, red and black pepper until blended.
Add soup; stir well. Fold in crabmeat, shrimp and rice.
Spoon into greased casserole. Dot with oleo and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake twenty minutes at 400°.
Crabmeat may be omitted and use 2 cups shrimp instead.

title: no-bake cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa together for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: crisp zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into patties and fry in oil until brown.

title: halloween face paint
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: cherry macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg, evaporated milk, sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until smooth.
Pour pie filling into pie crust, then pour beaten mixture over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until middle is firm.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Thaw frozen juices and add to all other juices; stir and refrigerate in plastic container(s).
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale when guests arrive.
You may add packets of Equal or Sweet 'N Low according to desired taste.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on high for 5 hours.
Drain juice and shred meat with fork, if necessary. Place on toasted hoagie/sub buns.
Cover with grated cheese and broil until cheese melts.

title: butter nut toffee
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients in pan.
Boil to crackling stage (300° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; add 1 cup nuts and pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Add melted chocolate over top and spread.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: lazy gal stew
directions: Remove all fat from meat (do not saute).
Place in large (2-quart) casserole in order listed, stirring after each addition. (Other vegetables may be "hunked" and used also.)

title: tuna fish scallop
directions: Boil carrots and onion together in liquid from peas.
After 10 minutes, add cubed potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Make white sauce of flour, butter, milk, salt and lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler for 15 minutes.
If any juice is left in vegetables, substitute for part of milk.
Add drained peas to other vegetables.
Break fish into small pieces and mix in white sauce. In buttered dish, layer vegetables, sauce and repeat.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: rendang padang (spicy curry beef)
directions: Heat oil in pan and add garlic, turmeric, ginger and lemon grass; saut lightly. Then add meat and crushed red peppers.

title: jello candy
directions: Chill and cut into squares (red, green and yellow are pretty colors for Christmas candy).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for a few minutes. Form into one large or 2 medium balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: pecan pie(2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs well and add remaining ingredients in order as they are listed.
Pour in pie shells and bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
May cover pie crust edges with tinfoil during baking time.
Center of pie may be slightly soft when taken from oven.

title: crab-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until top is slightly browned.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In small bowl mix soap and sour cream.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, heat margarine.
Add onion and chili powder. Cook until tender.
Add chicken, chilies and 2 tbsp soup mixture. Spread 1/2 c soup mixture in 2 qt shallow baking dish.
Along one side of each tortilla, spread about 1/4 c chicken mixture.
Roll up each tortilla around filling and place seam- side down in baking dish.
Spread remaining soup mixture over enchiladas. Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until hot.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken Soup

title: edna's pound cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add milk and dry ingredients a little at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well between each.
Line bottom of angel food pan with wax paper and not sides and stem.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door for 1 hour.
If cake doesn't spring back when touched, cook few minutes more.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together in a large bowl.
Add nuts and popcorn; mix well.
Spread on an ungreased pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 15 minutes.

title: herbed green beans
directions: In saucepan cook frozen green beans according to package directions; drain well.
In another saucepan cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in mushrooms, chopped pimiento, marjoram and basil and dash of pepper.
Stir in well drained beans.
Toss to coat; heat through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: Pour everything in the bowl and stir until thoroughly mixed, then refrigerate for about an hour.

title: fruit layered angel dessert
directions: Trim brown crust from cake and discard. Tear cake into 1-inch pieces. Prepare pudding according to package directions, then fold in 2 cups of whipped topping, reserving about 2 tablespoons for garnish.

title: roz's trash can cookies
directions: Cream eggs, butter, sugars and vanilla; add remaining ingredients. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: curried walnuts
directions: Heat oil in skillet and add nuts.
Cook slowly, stirring, until golden and crisp.
Drain.
Combine rest of ingredients and sprinkle over hot nuts.
Toss.
Cool before storing.
Makes a great Christmas gift!

title: south sea island chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand 3 to 4 hours.
At serving time toss with 1 large can Chinese noodles.
Serves 12.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add peppers, then add soups and simmer.
Add diced chicken.
Season to taste.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 quart casserole dish with Pam.
Place layer of chips on bottom.
Pour 1/3 chicken/soup mixture on top of chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat steps.
Place in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: triple good bar
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until the mixture begins to bubble. Remove from heat and put aside to cool slightly.
Beat oleo, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until evenly mixed and crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan.
Spread raisin mixture over oatmeal layer.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture; pat lightly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Can be frozen.

title: maple country ribs
directions: Place ribs in large kettle or Dutch oven. Cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Drain. Place ribs in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; combine in mixing bowl the cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size.
Stir dough down.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round 2-quart casserole.
Let rise in warm place until light.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 or 50 minutes.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: orange sauce(diabetic recipe)
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Add orange juice concentrate and orange drink mix.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
Use as a glaze on poultry or pork.

title: lemon sauce for gingerbread
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, lemon rind and lemon juice in double boiler.
Bring
water
to a boil.
Turn heat to low and cook until
margarine melts and sugar dissolves.
Stir often. Stir in eggs
and
cook, stirring constantly, for 5 to 7 minutes,
or until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Serve warm over gingerbread or pound cake.	Yields 1 2/3 cups.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Mold into 1 large loaf or 2 small ones. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: peanut pie(yields one 9-inch pie)
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and add peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold whipped topping into mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles.
Slice pickles and put back in the jar.
Add the remaining ingredients and shake until the sugar is dissolved.
These come out good and crispy.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Put cut biscuits in margarine and let set while rolling the others.
Roll each into a ball and then in sugar-nut-cinnamon mixture and place in a greased tube pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave pecans
directions: In a large dish, put unbeaten egg white, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt and stir together.
Add pecans and stir to coat.
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, all together 6 to 6 1/2 minutes.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and almond extract. Pour into a greased 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool for 10 minutes.
Beat sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of baked cream cheese.
Return to oven for 20 minutes.
When cool, top with fresh fruit such as strawberries, blueberries, pineapple, etc.

title: stonny's tomato salsa
directions: Mix and refrigerate; will keep for several days.
This makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: hot and spicy marinade
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients, stirring to blend well.
Great on chicken or beef.

title: beet pickles
directions: Select small, young, tender beets.
Cook until tender and the skins slip easily.
Dip in cold water.
Slip off skins.
Make syrup of sugar, water and vinegar.
Add spices in cheesecloth bag. Add beets and cook 10 minutes.
Pack beets into hot jars.
Add boiling syrup to within 1/2-inch of jar top.
Close.
Process in boiling water for 20 minutes if whole, 5 minutes if sliced.
Start to count processing time as soon as water returns to boiling.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Crush 36 cookies in bowl; add melted margarine.
Mix together and press on bottom and up sides of 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust. Let ice cream get creamy, then put ice cream on pie crust.
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Warm and spread chocolate topping over ice cream.
Then put Cool Whip over topping.
Crush a few leftover cookies and sprinkle over Cool Whip.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix yolks and 1 cup sugar.
Slowly add milk while stirring. Place pot on low fire.
Add vanilla pudding, 1 tablespoon nutmeg and 2 tablespoons vanilla.
Stir and let get good and hot.
Do not boil.
Beat egg whites and add 1 cup sugar gradually until good and foamy.
Put in pot with milk.
Mix with mixer for a few seconds and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese (room temperature) in mixing bowl until creamed.
Add powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Beat until real smooth.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°. Needs no icing.

title: brownies
directions: For
Fudge Type Brownies:
In large mixing bowl mix all dry ingredients except
sugar.
In separate large bowl combine sugar, butter, cocoa
and
eggs until fluffy, then combine dry ingredients with sugar
mixture.
Mix
well, then add vanilla. Pour into 9 x 13-inch
greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Bump pan when brownies start to rise.

title: apple pie breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 X 13 pan.
In a large bowl, mix together brown sugar, 1 tsp. cinnamon and one shake of ground cloves.
Mix in melted butter.
Stir in the apples and raisins until evenly coated.
Pour into greased pan.
Arrange bread slices in an even layer over the fruit.
Whisk together eggs, milk, vanilla and 2 tsp. cinnamon.
Pour over bread making sure all pieces are soaked. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator (let sit out while oven preheats) and preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Bake covered for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and cook another 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 more minutes before serving.

title: oven-fried chicken strips
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Melt margarine in oven in 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix all other ingredients, except chicken, in large bowl. Coat chicken in flour mixture. Place in baking dish. Bake 15 minutes. Flip and bake 15 minutes more.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into Bundt pan sprayed with Pam. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan. While still warm, poke holes in cake with ice pick or skewer. Pour on glaze.

title: iced tea
directions: Mix tea with drink powder mix, lemonade and sugar.
Add water. Cool with ice cubes and serve.

title: crabmeat elegance
directions: Set aside crabmeat.
Mix all other ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Garnish with fresh, chopped chives.
Perfect with crackers, vegetables or chips.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese, gradually adding powdered sugar.
Chill mixture for 1 hour.
Fold cheese mixture and Cool Whip together adding the vanilla.
Put into pie shells.
Top with pie filling.
Makes 2 pies; freezes well.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce, stirring half of the mixture into the ground beef with the chilies, half of the cheese and half of the onions.
Mix well.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown the hamburger, bacon and onion.
Mix together brown sugar, ketchup, barbecue sauce, pepper, mustard, chili powder and salt.
Mix and pour over meat; add butter beans, pork and beans and kidney beans.
Mix all, then crumble bacon over top.
Bake in oven.
"I cook it in a crock-pot on slow."

title: hand cranked ice cream
directions: Scald milk and sugar in a large pot.
Beat well the eggs.

Add gradually to hot milk mixture (first add a few spoonfuls of hot mixture to egg to prevent curdling). Add cream, salt and vanilla. Beat thoroughly. Fill freezer container to 2 1/2-inches below the top of the container to avoid overflow.
Put ice around container after closing and put salt over ice.
Start turning handle.
When it gets too hard to turn the crank, stop and wrap the whole freezer with sacks and let it finish freezing.

title: speedy quiche
directions: Saute Spam, onions and green pepper in oil until vegetables are tender.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Pour evenly into pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: Press 1/3 of crust mixture into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Turn oven to 475°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf from sauce.

title: cucumber sandwich pickles
directions: In large mixing bowl, place prepared cucumber slices.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add 2 quarts water and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and rinse.
In a 2-quart casserole, place cucumbers, vinegar and 1 cup water.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 10 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes, until tender.
Drain.

title: one-dish chicken 'n gravy
directions: Dip chicken in flour.
Place skin down in melted butter in 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 425°. Turn chicken, bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onions and mushrooms to chicken.
Mix milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Beat egg whites to a peak.
Mix sugar and flavor with egg whites.
Fold in crackers and pecans.
Cook crust for approximately 12 to 15 minutes (until firm, but not hard).
Cream butter, cream cheese and whipped cream together until smooth.
Spread mixture onto cooled crust.
Add fruit topping of your choice.

title: reese's cup cake
directions: Heat until bubbly margarine, cocoa, eggs, buttermilk and water.
Combine sugar, flour and soda; stir into heated mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Bake in greased 10 x 15-inch pan for 25 minutes or in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend together peanut butter and cooking oil; spread on cake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine shrimp and lemon juice.
Mix shrimp with a fork until smooth.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well. Add shrimp and Tabasco.
Stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry pie
directions: Beat butter; add sugar and beat again.
Add melted chocolate and and vanilla and beat.
Add 1 egg.
Beat exactly 3 minutes and add other egg.
Beat exactly 3 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker or regular pie shell and chill at least 5 hours or overnight. Very good and very rich.

title: snack mix
directions: In large paper bag, mix together cereals, pretzels and nuts along with garlic salt, seasonal salt and cheese.
Empty bag into a large bowl and place butter and Worcestershire sauce over mixture; combine gently with your hands.
Empty bowl into a 4 qt slow cooker and cook on low for 3-4 hours.
Tear open the bag originally used to mix snack.
Mix and spread flat on a counter. Spread heated snack mix onto bag and let dry for a minimum of 1 hour; letting the paper absorb excess mixture.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 10 cups.
tags: bite size crispy corn cereal squares
bite size crispy rice cereal squares

title: coleslaw - golden rule
directions: Spread shredded cabbage, chopped onion and chopped green pepper in a flat casserole dish.
Sprinkle the sugar evenly over all.
Combine vinegar, oil, salt, dry mustard and celery seed. Bring to boil and pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand 2 hours. Stir mixture, then refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potpourri
directions: *Lavender, orrisroot (which is a scent preservative, get at pharmacy), tonka bean, sandalwood, lemon verbena and sage.

title: banana cake with caramel icing
directions: Cream butter, sugar and bananas together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add soda, dissolved in buttermilk, then add flour and baking powder sifted together.
Bake in moderate oven in layers or loaf pans.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Mix and bring to rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Put 1 pint marshmallow cream in a bowl.
(I use the 7 ounce size jar of marshmallow cream.)
Pour syrup over and mix well, stirring and beating until it loses its gloss.
Add 1/2 cup or more of chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar and sauerkraut.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion together.
Put chips into 9 x 13-inch pan and crush.
Cream together tomatoes, beans, chicken and mushroom soup.
Put hamburger and onion on chips, then rest of ingredients.
Top off with cheese.
Put into oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Combine filling ingredients, tossing lightly. Chill.
Cut thin slice from top of buns; hollow out insides.
Toast buns.
Spread with cream cheese; add crisp leaf of lettuce.
Then fill with chilled salad mixture.

title: punch
directions: In blender, blend bananas, pineapple, orange juice, lemonade, Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add water to make 1 gallon.
Put in freezer for several hours.
Stir once.
Should have fine ice particles throughout.
Do not freeze solid.
Before serving, mix with 7-Up.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients and stir to blend.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown meat until done; drain.
Add rice, beans and cheese. Heat on low burner until cheese melts.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water. Beat smooth. Add flour and pecans.
Mix well. Roll in small balls. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown on the bottom. Roll in powdered sugar and store in tight container.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Grate potatoes coarsely and mix with other ingredients.
Put in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
These are delicious!

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add soup.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to butter and syrup; mix.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost.

title: heath bar cake
directions: I freeze Heath bars, then put them in plastic baggie and use kitchen hammer (not too fine).
Bake cake according to box directions.
