Remove from oven and using soda straw, make holes all over top of cake.
Pour Mrs. Richardson's sundae topping over top of cake.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip to top of cake, then crumbled Heath bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: viennese crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix thoroughly together.
Add flour, almonds and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Spoon out small pieces of dough and shape with fingers into small crescents about 2 inches long and 3/4 inch high.
Arrange on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
While still warm, roll each cookie in confectioners sugar.
Let cool, then roll again in confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: pink fruit compote
directions: Cut skin from pear, chop and puree in blender.
Strain through sieve into large bowl.
Stir in sugar and lime juice until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in remaining fruits.
Serve immediately. Contains 105 calories.

title: vegetable - beef soup
directions: Cook and stir beef in oil in Dutch oven over medium heat until brown.
Stir in beef broth, salt, marjoram, thyme, pepper and bay leaf; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Place cottage cheese in large bowl with lid.
Pour dry gelatin over it and mix gently.
Add pineapple and oranges; mix gently, then fold in Cool Whip and seal.

title: apple cake with caramel frosting
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add eggs.
Measure and sift dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and chopped apples.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread dough rise.
Rub with Crisco on dough in pan.
Roll out dough.
Brush with egg.
Layer sliced ham, Provolone cheese, pepperoni and American cheese.
Sprinkle oregano, Italian seasonings and grated cheese.
Roll like jelly roll.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: curried beef stew
directions: Place meat in a large kettle.
Add all ingredients and cover. When mixture comes to steaming point, reduce heat to simmer.
Stir occasionally.
Should more liquid be needed, add either water or tomato juice.
This mixture should end more like a thick sauce than a thin mixture.
Serve over hot rice.
Serve with chutney, ground peanuts or coconut, sprinkled over the top.
Cooking time is 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: punch
directions: Place strawberries in blender.
Process until smooth.
(Can be done earlier and stored in refrigerator.)
Mix strawberries, lemonade and pineapple juice in punch bowl.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add 7-Up very slowly.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.
Also good with raspberries.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese well.
Add other ingredients.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans and chill.
Can be frozen.

title: easy chocolate cake -- good!
directions: Add flour, sugar, Crisco, salt, cocoa and 3/4 cup milk together and beat vigorously by hand or mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Grease and flour two or three round cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: cocoa drops(microwave)
directions: In a glass bowl, microwave milk and margarine for 45 seconds. Add sugar and cocoa.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Microwave for 3 minutes or until just boiling.
Cool 1 minute.
Blend in peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in oats.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper and chill until firm.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in bottom of pan.
Bake approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Combine 1/4 cup chopped nuts and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Roll ball through mixture. Chill.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add yolk and stir. Then add flour and vanilla. Fold into potato chips and nuts, if desired. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes in 350° oven. Do not let cookies brown. While still warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar, approximately 4 dozen.

title: vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir in cheese.
Heat until cheese melts and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until soft.
Drain.
Mix squash, onion, salt, 1/2 grated cheese, 1/2 crackers, and milk.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with remaining crackers and cheese.	Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: avocado lime salad
directions: Use pineapple juice as part of liquid for jello.
Mix all ingredients together, then let congeal in refrigerator.
Good and different!!

title: brownie nuggets
directions: Place the cocoa in a saucepan and gradually add the milk, stirring well.
Stir in the sugar and margarine and bring the mixture to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in the oatmeal and peanut butter.
Quickly drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Makes about 25 cookies.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and pour into three greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Do not overcook.
Sometimes, 15 minutes is long enough.)

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Combine oleo with boiling water and cool.
Add 1 cup cold water, sugar, salt and eggs to yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add 7 1/2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. When ready to use, take out amount you want to make on floured dough board or cabinet.
Roll out to desired size.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Butter before baking for even cooking.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Saute seasoning in oleo or butter until soft.
Add soup and cheese and add milk, a little at a time, until cheese is melted and all is well blended.
Add salt and pepper while cooking.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with coffee.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in loaf pan.

title: coco caramel squares
directions: Melt in a double boiler:
caramels and 5 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Mix cake mix with melted margarine, 5 tablespoons evaporated milk and nuts.
Spread half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread with 1 cup of semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Spread melted caramels over chocolate.
Dot with remaining cake batter. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: linguine with knockout garlic pesto
directions: Put garlic, basil, parsley and pine nuts in food processor for 15 seconds.
With machine on, pour 3/4 cup olive oil through feeding tube.
Add cheese and rest of olive oil.
Process until mixed.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk; bring to rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add marshmallows, 5 at a time, then chips, vanilla and nuts.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter biscuits and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Arrange in a Bundt pan in layers.
In skillet, melt oleo and brown sugar.
Drizzle this over biscuits as you arrange them in pan and on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add lemon juice and grated rind, hot water, 1/4 cup sugar and flour.
Put flour and salt in sugar. Cook in double boiler until slightly thickened.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; fold into cooked mixture.
Beat egg whites before cooking custard.
Put in cooked pie shell and brown at 325°.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in small pieces.
Cook until tender. Add nutmeg, vanilla and sugar.
Put 1 stick margarine in baking dish and melt in oven.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 cup self-rising flour.
Add milk to form a loose batter.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Put potatoes on top of batter.
Bake until brown on top in 400° oven.

title: won't stay around long cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a large hole in middle. Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand; do not beat.
Grease and flour
a large tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350°.
Top will crack open and color will be brown when done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cream cheese icing.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with 1/4 cup margarine and corn flake crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: triple fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. In a saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Heat just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add semi-sweet chocolate chips and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in white chocolate and milk chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased brownie pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pat's sugarless cake
directions: Beat together the salad oil, sweetener, egg and buttermilk. Sift together the flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda and add to liquid ingredients.
Add diced prunes or dates and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate sour cream
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, eggs and sour cream until fluffy.
Add soda, vanilla and cocoa.
Mix in flour and then walnuts.
Drop by ice cream scoop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, ice with chocolate fudge frosting.

title: potato bites
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Do not peel.
Cut into 1-inch cubes. Melt oleo in pan.
Put potatoes in pan and stir with spoon until evenly coated with oleo.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle generously with Lawry's salt, lots of Parmesan cheese and then paprika.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and let sit there for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zesty shrimp rice salad
directions: Place unopened rice pouch in boiling water in saucepan.
Do not cover.
Bring water to boil and heat for 16 minutes.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, layer crushed noodles, coleslaw, almonds, sunflower seeds and green onions. In separate bowl, mix oil, sugar, vinegar and 2 beef flavorings from noodle packs. Mix well. Pour over salad. Do not stir until next day. Keep, covered, overnight.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
To this, add pineapple (juice and all).
Blend well.
Add small tub Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: cooked ice cream custard
directions: Heat milk and butter to a skim stage.
Add blended flour and sugar to beaten eggs.
Pour into kettle with milk.
Bring to a hard boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add cans of evaporated milk and condensed milk with vanilla.
Cool in refrigerator.
Pour into a 5-quart ice cream maker.
Add salt and ice to freeze custard (around outside of canister).

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk. Mix well and store in refrigerator in airtight container.
Do not stir before using.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Keeps well.
Use as needed.

title: parmesan tomatoes
directions: Remove stems from tomatoes and slice in half crosswise. Place, cut side up, in a small baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients.
Sprinkle over tops of tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: oyster soup
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and water; blend well to make a smooth paste.
Simmer oysters and the liquid they are packed in until the edges of oysters curl.
Add slowly the paste to oysters, stirring to prevent lumps.
Pour this mixture into the scalded milk and remove from heat.
Cover; let stand for 15 minutes to improve the flavor.
Reheat briefly, adding the butter.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: kellogg's special k bars
directions: Measure corn syrup and brown sugar into large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Add Kellogg's Special K cereal and raisins. Stir until well coated. With back of spoon, press mixture evenly and firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Let stand until cool. Cut into bars.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter. Mix together. Add other ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese, sour cream and Italian seasoning.
Spread evenly in a 9 or 10-inch glass dish.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and green pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serve with crackers, corn chips, or tortilla chips.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato thing
directions: Mash potatoes; beat eggs until fluffy.
Add all ingredients to potatoes and blend well (by stirring).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Combine flour, mustard, salt and a little pepper in a shallow dish.
Dredge chops in this mixture and set aside.
In a 3 1/2 quart slow cooker, combine remaining flour mixture and broth. Pour oil in a large skillet.
Place over medium high heat until hot.
Cook chops until browned on both sides and place in slow cooker.
Cook on high 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serve with hot rice or mashed potatoes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix cheese crackers, butter and almonds and put on top of bean mixture. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: christmas candy
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls and let stand until they get firm.
Melt the chocolate and paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate and lay on waxed paper.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: Boil fruit salad with salt.
Dissolve jello in hot fruit salad.
Let mixture begin to set.
Mash cream cheese and enough of the whipped cream to make smooth.
Fold cream cheese and remainder of whipped cream into gelatin mixture.
Mold and congeal.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, rice, onion, 1/2 tomato sauce, egg and spices.
Boil large head of cabbage until leaves are limp.
Roll approximately 1/4 cup meat mixture into cabbage leaves.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix sugar, flour and pineapple in a casserole dish.
Add cheese and sprinkle with small amount of juice over the mixture. Cover with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted oleo over this.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple orange bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cream the shortening. Add sugar gradually. Add egg.
Beat thoroughly. Add dry ingredients and orange juice alternately. Blend well after each addition. Add nuts, raisins, grated orange rind and apples. Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Makes 3 small loaves or 1 large loaf.
Especially moist and tasty.

title: flautas
directions: Cook meat with salt and pepper in boiling water until done. Cool meat and blend it.
Warm tortillas in microwave.

title: poppy seed lemon bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or 3 small loaf pans.

title: layered salad
directions: Put lettuce on bottom of oblong dish.
Follow this with the water chestnuts, the celery, green onions and peas.
Mix the mayonnaise with the salt, pepper and sugar.
Spread this on top of pea layer, making sure top and edges are sealed with this mixture. Put cheeses on top.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onions, salt and pepper.
Drain grease off and add chili seasoning to meat.
Add beans (drain and rinse), tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 45 minutes.
If too thick, add a little water.

title: over-the-hill gang supper
directions: Amount of ingredients depends on the size of the crowd.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Mix melted margarine and bread crumbs and spread on casserole.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar into corn meal and mix well in a large bowl.
Combine eggs, cream-style corn and milk in smaller bowl and mix well.
Add to flour mixture together with crackling, oil and baking soda, if using buttermilk, be sure everything is well combined.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch square or round cake pan, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown and tests done.

title: smoothie
directions: Cover fruit with fruit juice.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend all together until smooth. Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: First, mix salt, cinnamon, allspice and cloves with graham cracker crumbs, then add fruit, dates and coconut.
Mix well until coated good with crumbs.
Add Eagle Brand and mix well.
With a spoon, put into a loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Add a little mixture at a time; press evenly into pan with spoon so as not to have any air pockets.
Continue until filled at least 3/4 full.
Makes 1 small loaf and 4 mini loaves or 2 small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Remove, cool and wrap in wax paper and foil to freeze or store in refrigerator.
Best made a month ahead so to season.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potato slices and seasoning sauce into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to boiling.
Stir into potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pastry shell in very hot oven at 450° for about 5 to 7 minutes, until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and reduce heat to 325°.
Fry bacon and onion until bacon is crisp; drain.
Place in pie shell.
Add cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over those in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until almost set in the middle.
Cool 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy caramel frosting
directions: Cook butter and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Add milk and stir until it comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add enough powdered sugar to spread.

title: sweet dough
directions: Place yeast, warm water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in a bowl.
Let set until bubbly, about 10 minutes.
In a large bowl or pan, add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and oleo.
Pour over all this 1 1/2 cups warm milk and blend well.
Add eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir well.
Add half of flour.
Beat smooth.
Add rest of flour, cup at a time until it's smooth and have soft dough.
Knead until smooth elastic like.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning dough grease side up. Cover and let rise until dough doubles in size in warm place. Punch down, then let rise again.

title: chocolate pots de creme
directions: Melt chocolate in milk over low heat.
Add sugar and salt; cook until choocolate is completley melted.
Remove from heat. Add egg yolks gradually, stirring.
Cook over very low heat until pudding thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into custard cups or serving dishes.
Chill until set.
Serve with cream or whipped cream.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
Mix in tomatoes.
Add layer of macaroni and tomato to pan; add slices of cheese on top. Add another layer on top; add slices of cheese.
Add another layer of macaroni and tomato.
When you get to top of pan, add final layer of cheese.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sugar pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet. Saute vegetables for 30 minutes. Add seasonings to taste.
Add crawfish and saute for 1 minute. Stir in flour and saute for 3 minutes. Add water and bouillon cubes. Simmer 10 or 15 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Cream together cheese, salt, pepper, onion, pineapple and 1 cup nuts.
Mix well and shape into ball.
Roll in 1 cup nuts. Refrigerate at least 1 day before serving.

title: pumpkin patch dessert
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix over evenly.
Pour the melted butter over the cake mix evenly.
Sprinkle with the chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Can be served with whipped cream. Makes 18 to 24 servings.

title: chicken sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place leaf of lettuce in pita bread.
Spoon mixture on lettuce.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine oatmeal, water and butter; let set about 10 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Add sugars and eggs to cereal mixture.
Add flour; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Spread Coconut Topping evenly on top of hot cake; continue to cook about 20 minutes until lightly browned or broil 1 to 2 minutes to brown top.
Cool completely.

directions: Melt

Add brown sugar and

cook for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and pour over confectioners sugar.
Beat well until smooth and then spread on cake.

title: diet strawberry mousse
directions: Pour milk in a mixing bowl and freeze until ice forms around the edges.
Whip with mixer until fluffy and peaks form when the beaters are taken out.
Fold in lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add strawberries and sweetener.
Fold in and pour in a lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: turkey chili
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onions; saute 5 minutes.
Add turkey; cook, stirring 8 to 10 minutes. Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer half an hour.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Boil until it forms hard ball.
Add marshmallows, pecans and cherries.

title: cold chicken with ginger sauce
directions: Bring water, 1 tablespoon salt and ginger to boil.
Add whole chicken.
Cover and immediately turn to lowest heat for 25 minutes. Turn chicken over and allow to stand another 25 minutes at lowest heat, covered.
Remove chicken from broth and rinse quickly with cold water; drain.
Freeze broth for later use or add vegetables and serve as a first course soup.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and margarine to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and stir by hand until it forms a ball.
Let cool (10 minutes).
When cool, stir in unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Pour mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°. Let cool.
Beat together pudding and milk until thick.
Blend in softened cream cheese.
Spread mixture into crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
When ready to serve, drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: lemon-pineapple sheet
directions: Dough:
Mix flour, oleo and water, blend mixture together and spread into 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Prick dough with fork and bake until brown at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Add all dry ingredients in bowl, then add other ingredients. Mix well with mixer.
Add grated rind and chopped nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan with wax paper in bottom. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: deli vegetable roll-ups
directions: Spread about 2 tablespoons cream cheese spread over each tortilla. Layer with tomato, peppers, olives, cheeses and pickle slices. Drizzle with salad dressing. Top with lettuce, turkey and salami. Roll up tightly. Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with additional dressing, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave for 9 minutes, stirring once.
Mix all ingredients, except noodles together.
Pour into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with noodles and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate haystacks no-bake cookies
directions: Mix 1/3 cup coconut and the noodles in a medium size bowl. Add melted chocolate; stir with rubber spatula until well blended. Using spatula, drop 12 mounds (2 tablespoons each) noodle mixture onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Press mounds lightly to compact.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour until firm.
Can be stored at room temperature.
Makes 12.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In one bowl, mix together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, beat the oil and eggs until foamy.
Stir in the apples and sugar.
Add this to the flour mixture.
Stir in the vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: gorp
directions: Mix 1 box or package of each.
This is a high energy, high nutrition, eat-out-of-hand food for hiking or camping (or any other time).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and chopped onion for 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots, if using, and fold in squash and onion mix.
Melt butter and add to stuffing.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 11 x 8 x 2-inch or 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon in vegetable mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour, salt, margarine and pecans well.
Press into oblong dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° until golden brown (approximately 20 minutes).

title: chilly dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl beat cottage cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Cover.
Chill before serving. Serve with nacho chips or Vegetable Dunkers.

title: rachel's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Coat breasts with seasonings, cheese, parsley and bread crumbs.
Place in single layer in pan.
Mix water, oil and oleo. Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Cover and let set overnight.

title: chili
directions: Let simmer 2 hours.
Brown ground beef in skillet and brown onion in pan you use to cook it all in with the 3 tablespoons shortening.

title: pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle.
Sift dry ingredients together into bowl or pitcher.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Slowly mix into dry ingredients.
Stir well.
When griddle is ready, pour to desired size cake.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix lightly the potatoes, salt and mayonnaise.
Set in refrigerator until serving time.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix and add more mayonnaise, if needed.
Serve on lettuce garnished with tomato wedges and sliced hard-boiled egg.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook onion in bacon grease until soft.
Add chicken broth; heat to boiling.
Add cubed cheese and, stirring continually, heat until melted.
Mix the arrowroot, cornstarch or flour well with half and half or some water.
Add half and half, cooked broccoli, mushrooms and thickening mixture.
Heat until serving temperature reached; stir occasionally.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: snack mix
directions: Combine melted butter, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Stir in cereal, peanuts and pretzels.
Bake at 250° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and store in a tight container or Ziploc bag.
Makes 8 cups.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cut ham and pepperoni into small pieces.
Mix with Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
Roll out thawed bread dough into a rectangle.
Sprinkle with pepper and meat/cheese mixture.
Roll dough up.
Seal the edge with a little water and pinch to keep the stuffing inside.
Oil cookie sheet and rub oil on top of dough.
Place dough on cookie sheet.
Bend into a horseshoe shape if necessary.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Slice after some cooling.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Separate biscuits and place in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press biscuits over bottom and 1-inch up sides. Seal perforations.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Blend plain yogurt, horseradish, salt and pepper. Spread over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's chiffon pie
directions: Chill Pet milk.
Mix and cook until melted other ingredients. Whip chilled milk and mix together with other ingredients.
Place in a wafer crust; chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a bowl, mix the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1 tablespoon
sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: baked ziti for two
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ziti in boiling water for 12 to 16 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Cook half of sauce and all of the Parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano, basil, salt, pepper and egg at medium heat until well mixed.
Toss in ziti until well coated. Pour mixture in 9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inch bread pan.
Top with rest of the sauce and the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 8 minutes.

title: pineapple dream pie(diet)
directions: In small bowl, combine flaked coconut and margarine; press on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake coconut pie shell in 325° oven about 15 minutes or until golden; cool.

title: pork, beef or chicken barbecue
directions: Cook first three ingredients until tender.
When meat is done, remove from bone.
Shred with fork.
Return to crock-pot and add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Let simmer for 3 or 4 hours or longer.
This makes delicious sandwiches served on buns.

title: cheese cookies #1
directions: Blend cheese and oleo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop from spoon small bite-size pieces.
Can put pecan half on each cookie.
Bake 18 minutes at 325°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish. Bake approximately 40 minutes or until light golden brown in a 350 degree oven.

title: velvet custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
At once, pour into unbaked pie shell.
To avoid spills, fill at oven.
Dash top with nutmeg (optional).
Bake in very hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce to 425° and bake 10 minutes or until knife inserted comes clean.
Cool on rack and chill.

title: "dear hearts" seafood bisque(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan; add onion and cook gently for 5 minutes or until softened. Add artichokes, broth and wine.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until artichokes are tender and a leaf pulls away easily.
Process mixture in food processor or blender until smooth.
Return soup to saucepan. Stir in shellfish, cream, parsley, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Simmer very gently, uncovered, over low heat 5 to 10 minutes. Do not boil or shellfish will become tough.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: If using fresh tomatoes, peel and chop.
Wash and slice okra into rounds about 1/2-inch thick.
Saute onion and okra in grease until browned.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add water if necessary to prevent sticking.
If too juicy, uncover and cook a little longer.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: victorian raspberry coffee cake
directions: With a pastry blender, cut cream cheese and margarine into Bisquick mix until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk gradually, stirring with a fork.
Gather dough together.
Turn dough, cut onto lightly floured surface and knead 5 times.
Wrap dough with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
On waxed paper, roll dough to a 6 x 1-inch rectangle.
Turn onto a greased baking sheet; remove waxed paper.
Spread raspberry preserves down center of dough.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts over preserves. Make 1-inch cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides; fold strips over filling.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Remove tinfoil before cooling.
Drizzle the warm coffee cake with icing.
Combine confectioners sugar, vanilla and enough milk to make of drizzling consistency.

title: orange rusks
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and orange rind.
Butter both sides of bread strips.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in the oven or until crisp.

title: gingerbread 1
directions: Put oil, sugar, molasses and spices in bowl; beat until syrupy.
Add flour, soda and salt sifted together alternately with buttermilk.
Put in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until it tests done.
(There are no eggs in the recipe.)

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Put in refrigerator until syrupy. Whip until fluffy. Beat sherbet into mixture; beat well. Fold in whipped cream and oranges. Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: cherry brownie snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Geaase bottom and sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with shortening.
Stir brownie mix, pie filling and egg in large bowl until well mixed.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Stir almond extract and food coloring into frosting. Spread over cake.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Beat oil and sugar; add baking soda and baking powder, cinnamon and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp and tender.
Place spears in baking dish with tips pointing out.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder in mixing bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and sift baking powder, flour and salt.
Add milk and well beaten egg; mix well.
Pare and core the apples.
Cut in sections and dip each piece of apple in the batter.
Fry in deep fat at 340° to 350° until brown.
Drain on unglazed paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Add oats, soda and salt; stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by 1/4 cupfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
You can also drop by teaspoonfuls.
This recipe makes about 7 dozen of these smaller cookies.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add garlic, tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Add water to lard; break down with fork.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to lard mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Will make 1 double crust and 1 pie shell.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix softened butter, peanut butter, Fluff and powdered sugar. Shape into balls.
Dip into melted chips; drop onto waxed paper.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples; sprinkle with flour and spices.
Blend in thawed undiluted juice.
Put into bottom crust and dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: the dish tegluni
directions: Brown onion, garlic, pepper and ground beef.
Boil noodles according to directions on package and drain.

Combine with ground beef mixture and add tomato paste, mushrooms, olives, cinnamon, salt, tomatoes and corn and put in a 17 x 11 2 1/4 inch pan. Cover with slices of cheese and bake 1/2 hour at 350 degrees or until cheese has melted.

title: cheezy, crusty chili casserolettes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: ironworker chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift into bowl sugar, flour and salt.
Mix in saucepan on stove margarine, shortening, cocoa and water.
Stir in rolling boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon, and vanilla.
Bake in 16 x 11-inch cookie sheet with sides at 350° for 20 minutes.
Ice as soon as cake is removed from oven.

title: vegetable macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse and drain.
Cook peas according to directions; drain.
Combine all ingredients and toss gently. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick tropical cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9X13 pan with nonstick cooking spray. Spread pineapple in prepared pan. Top with pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over cherries, then drizzle butter over top. Sprinkle coconut over all. Bake for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fruity pebble treats
directions: Microwave butter for 1 minute.
Add marshmallows and salt. Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add Fruity Pebbles.
Put in 13 x 9-inch dish until firm.
Yield: 16 squares.
M-m-m good!!!

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Use 3 level spoons tea per mug and boiling water.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Blend together.
Put in serving bowl.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top. Chill approximately 1 hour.
Cut apples into slices when dip is ready to serve and then dip into.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits and salt 5 minutes in 2 1/2 cups boiling water. Take off burner and melt in cheese and butter.
Add milk and eggs. Mix thoroughly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until brown.
Double recipe for company.
Mix ahead and bake before meal.

title: chili
directions: Fry suet, then chop up onion and fry in the fat.
Add ground beef, salt, chili powder and red pepper.
Cook until done.
Add to 6 pounds of cooked beans.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine milk, water and pudding. Beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipping cream. Layer about one cup pudding mixture in bowl. Add vanilla wafers, then bananas. Repeat; end with bananas, pudding, then wafers.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes for 4.
Omit butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased dish at 400° for 30 minutes.
